title: Hospitality Weekend Pass - April 15-16
description:
The Red Bull Air Race World Championship makes a welcome return to San Diego on the 15-16 April 2017. Set on the Pacific coast of Southern California the location provides the perfect backdrop for a race.

San Diego last hosted a Red Bull Air Race back in 2009 and proved extremely popular with the fans that have often asked when the Air Race would return, well 2017 is the answer.

Nicolas Ivanoff won in the skies above the Pacific coast back in 2009 and he'll be looking to do it again in 2017 when the Red Bull Air Race returns.



These prices will increase on Feb. 24. Don't miss out on this special early pricing. Get your tickets today!


The Sky Lounge

The Sky Lounge has been specifically tailored for discerning guests who desire the finest possible race experience. Unrivalled views of the racetrack, five-star service and celebrated international cuisine all come together in our tailored VIP lounge, giving you the very best in corporate hospitality and motorsport entertainment.



Sky Lounge Includes-


	Luxurious hospitality facilities with comfortable in- and outdoor seating
	Prime location with spectacular and privileged views of the racetrack
	Large selection of gourmet menus, including local specialities and delicacies
	Complimentary bar with a full drinks menu including soft drinks and a wide selection of alcoholic beverages
	Bar service at all times
	Transmission of the race, results and live commentary on TV screens and video wall
	High-quality sound system to fully experience and follow the race
	Entertainment program, including live interviews with pilots, athletes and interesting personalities
	Red Bull Air Race merchandise shop
	RBAR gift and a copy of the official Red Bull Air Race Magazine with stories, news and background information


The Aviator Club

Aviator Club is the second-tier hospitality option that still promises to fully immerse you in the race. It is located at the south tip of the North Embarcadero and is the place to watch the Air Race in a relaxed atmosphere. Aviator Club provides an exciting hospitality environment including an impressive vantage point, capable of witnessing every twist and turn as the pilots race through the track.



Aviator Club Includes-


	Hospitality facilities with comfortable outdoor seating
	Prime location with superb views of the racetrack
	Selection of menus, including international and local cuisine
	Complimentary bar including soft drinks and a selection of alcoholic beverages
	Transmission of the race, results and live commentary

title: Extreme Leadership CERTIFICATION
description:
In this powerful and transformational workshop, you’ll explore the key tenets of the Extreme Leadership Framework—LEAP: Cultivating Love, Generating Energy, Inspiring Audacity, and Providing Proof—and learn how to apply them to your personal and professional leadership challenges. And then, with personal coaching from Steve Farber and his team, you'll be given all the tools, resources, and experience you'll need to facilitate this workshop for others.

Why Become a Certified Facilitator of The Extreme Leadership Workshop?

1. You’re a consultant, coach, or trainer who’d like to either offer The Extreme Leadership Workshop to your clients and/or build a training and consulting business around it.

2. You work for a company or organization, and you’d like to offer the Extreme Leadership Workshop internally.

3. You have no intention to teach the workshop to others, but you’d like to dive deeper into Extreme Leadership and you’ll use the certification process for your own development.

At the end of this intensive, 4-day program, you’ll be licensed to offer this unique workshop to your clients, your company, your team, your colleagues, or your community; just as important, you’ll become part of The Extreme Leadership Institute community and our exclusive facilitator “tribe.”

The Certification process starts with your participation in the Extreme Leadership Workshop, followed by 3 full days of deep background knowledge, practice of the Workshop, coaching and feedback from Steve Farber and his team, group discussion, business and marketing strategy, and loads of laughter and celebration.

As a Certified Facilitator, You’ll receive:


	License to facilitate the Extreme Leadership Workshop wherever you choose
	Designation as a Certified Facilitator by The Extreme Leadership Institute
	Extreme Leadership Facilitator Guide
	Extreme Leadership Participant Materials
	A signed copy of The Radical Leap - 10th Anniversary Edition & The Radical Edge
	A digital copy of all facilitation materials, including PowerPoint slides and supporting videos.
	Extreme Leadership Institute Certificate of Completion
	Access to the Extreme Leader Facilitator Network, an online resource for sharing of best practices in facilitating Extreme Leadership.
	Exclusive wholesale rates for additional Extreme Leadership Institute products and resources
	Direct access to and support from Steve Farber and his team
	Potential to earn referral business from the Extreme Leadership Institute

At the end of our final morning session, you are invited to join Steve Farber for a celebration Barbecue at his home.



 Continental Breakfast and Lunch are included on all days.

title: Think RED Wine & Paint Party
description:
Hosted by ARTIST, NATHAN MOHLE and the THINK RED PROJECT

Back by fantastic demand! Please join us for an afternoon of instructed painting and gorgeous wine, all while making an impact on the San Diego HIV community. The event will be guided by professional artist, Nathan Mohle and will be held at the fabulous Fifty Seven Degrees, which is centrally located in the Middletown neighborhood and has ample on-site and street parking.

Quick facts:

	
	What's included? A guided, two-hour-ish painting class
	
	What's provided? All the necessary materials for painting (brushes, paints, canvas, etc.) and to keep yourself as clean as possible (plastic aprons, plastic table cloths, etc.) 
	
	Do I get to keep the painting? Yes! 
	
	Wait, I don't know how to paint? That's okay, that's why our experienced instructor guides you along, helping you create your painting.
	
	I can't make it but I want to support the cause. That's great -- here's how you can help:
	
		
		Promote: you can help us by sharing this event and getting others to attend. 
		
		Donate: if you would like to make a tax deductible donation to Think Red Project, click here.

	
	

100% of the proceeds support Think Red Project, a 501(c)(3) registered non-profit that raises funds and awareness for organizations that serve the local HIV/AIDS community. Participants must register, but those who just want to watch or enjoy a glass of wine are also welcome.

For questions please contact Think Red Project; Fifty Seven Degrees has generously provided the space but is not responsible for the event.

title: Tater Tots & Beer Festival - San Diego
description:
The most Delicious Tater Tots & Beer Festival is coming to Balboa Park, in San Diego, CA!

Come and sample dozens of domestic, imported and crafted beers and sample delicious tater tot creations for your guilty dining pleasure.

Combined with all of the beer you can legally drink, delicious tater tots, a side of live music and funtimes… this event will be a day you will never forget. You just may have dreams about it for a long time afterwards.

Event Times: 3p-6p

* Only 2,000 GA Tickets: Includes: Beer Passport, Tater Tot Sampling.

* Only 200 VIP Tickets: Includes: Beer Passport, Tater Tot Sampling and VIP Areas.

* Only 100 Designated Driver Tickets: Includes: Tater Tot Sampling, Soda/Water Stations.

THIS EVENT WILL SELL OUT! (We have limited capacity)

This is a 21 and over event. No babies. No strollers. No Exceptions. However, you can definitely let your inner-child out during the festival and have a blast.

* This event is about Drinking Responsibly. It is not about getting wasted. We have limited the sessions to 3hrs and will be distributing alcohol in a timely manner to avoid over-consumption. We will also cut anyone off who does not appear to be drinking responsibly. We want everyone to enjoy the event and get home safely.

* Drink Passport: Every state has different laws for how much anyone can be served during any special event. For our festivals, wherever applicable, we provide all patrons a passport to use for beer sampling. You will receive a stamp from the brewery each time you sample a beer. Depending on local liquor laws, patrons will be allowed to sample up to 30 options during the 3-hour session. Certain venues may have different requirements for this as well, and if so, will be posted on the event page of the particular event to let you know. We reserve the right to cut anyone off for any reason whatsoever.

People-Friendly SERVICE Dogs on leash are allowed.

This is a Beer Only Event... No Ciders will be offered. 

Also, we are not able to maintain a Gluten-Friendly Environment due to cross-contamination and cannot guarantee gluten-free beers.

Rain or Shine Event. NO REFUNDS.

title: The Poetry Brothel: San Diego
description:
The Poetry Brothel is a unique and immersive poetry event that takes poetry outside classrooms and lecture halls and places it in the lush interiors of a bordello. The Poetry Brothel presents a rotating cast of both male and female poets as “whores,” each operating within a carefully crafted character, who impart their work in public readings, spontaneous eruptions of poetry, and most distinctly, as purveyors of private poetry readings on beds, chaise lounges and in private rooms. For a small fee, all of the “poetry whores” are available for these sequestered readings at any time during the event. Of course, any true brothel needs a good cover; The Poetry Brothel’s is an immersive cabaret, offering a full bar, musicians, burlesque dancers, painters, actors, and fortune-tellers, with newly integrated themes, performances and installations at each event.

Doors open at 8pm; show starts at 8:30pm. Themed costumes and/or evening wear are encouraged but not required. This event is 21+.

For specific event details, please visit www.thepoetrybrothel.com/events.html.

title: EXTREME LEADERSHIP WORKSHOP -  San Diego CA
description:
Based on the work of best-selling leadership author, Steve Farber, the Extreme Leadership Workshop explores the key tenets of Farber’s work—LEAP: Cultivating Love, Generating Energy, Inspiring Audacity, and Providing Proof—and techniques to apply them to personal and professional leadership challenges.


The Extreme Leadership Workshop is for anyone who—regardless of your position or title—aspires to gain more success in business and beyond by learning how to elevate yourself and others to unprecedented levels of achievement and fulfillment.


In this dynamic workshop, you will:


	Gain deep knowledge of the Extreme Leadership Framework and learn how to apply it to create more success in your business and personal life.
	Clarify what’s important to you and your organization, and leverage it to energize and inspire yourself and others.
	Increase your understanding of the challenges and opportunities facing you and your organization, and learn how to lead yourself and others through them.
	Develop an Extreme Leader Action Plan to change your piece of the world for the better—in little and big ways.

Your Materials Include:


	
	Participant Workbook, to serve as your guidebook throughout the Workshop
	
	A Daily Handbook for Extreme Leaders, to use as an ongoing resource throughout your career.
	
	A signed copy of The Radical Leap Re-Energized by Steve Farber, to keep you inspired
	
	Wake Up Pad (WUP), to help you capture your thoughts, observations, and ideas
	
	A series of follow-up videos, sent to you throughout the year to keep you on track and reinforce key actions and commitments.

Continental Breakfast and Lunch are included in the price of the Workshop

What workshop participants have to say…

 “As a leader, I spend every day competing for customers and the greatest talent. People want to work with people who truly love what they do, the people they do it with & the people they do it for. The Extreme Leadership Workshop made me look inside my heart and discover that this is what I have always believed. LEAP will change my company, the lives of the people in it, and those of everyone it touches..”
	~Mike Strohl CEO, Entisys/Agile360
	“This workshop is the above-and-beyond of leadership. I have read books and attended leadership courses that talk about the 'what' and 'how' of leadership. This workshop is different - it talks about the "why" of leadership. I learned that leadership was a love affair to change the world! That was big for me. It was powerful. The whole workshop is based on this foundation - and then builds on the what and the how. I loved the structure and the content. With it, I believe I am ready to take the Leap!”
	~ K. Bubna, Sr. Director of Software Engineering
	“LEAP in action will propel companies beyond competitors' reach. Those who do tap the power of people doing what they truly love... boldly... together WILL change the world.”
	~ Sue Melone, President, Boldtrek

title: Teacher Training: From Roots to Branches
description:
Our Grow Your Own! teacher trainings equip garden educators and leaders with hands-on tools, resources, and exciting lesson plans to incorporate garden education into the classroom.

Thursday, February 9th, 2016, 3:30 to 5:00 PM at The Ecology Center!

This workshop covers the basics to Fruit Tree care and Potato Planting. Topics covered in this 1.5 hour training session include:

Fruit Tree Pruning: why it’s important to prune your fruit trees and how to do it.

Fruit Tree Planting: What to plant and when.

Grafting: the basics of adding variety.

Potato Planting: how to maintain a potato tub for a healthy crop of spuds.

Interested in learning more about our Grow Your Own! program? Join a growing movement and engage in a hands-on teacher training experience. Contact Meg@theecologycenter.org for more info.

title: 2nd Annual Comedy Roast for Charity
description:
Come watch our friend and generous member of our community, Ted Kaplan, get roasted by friends, actors and A List Comedians! This event will not only be a lot of fun, it will be an opportunity for us to acknowledge Ted and his generous contributions here in the Los Angeles area and world wide. All proceeds will benefit Claire's Place Foundation, a charity committed to raising awareness and supporting children living with cystic fibrosis.

Our Second Annual Roast for Charity will take place at the beautiful Oliver Cafe and Lounge in the  Equinox Gym, West LA (Formerly Sports Club LA).  Oliver blends sexiness, sophistication and style  to create one  of the hottest dining destinations in Beverly Hills, West Los Angeles and Irvine!



Tickets are limited and this will definitely sell out quickly.  Book your ticket today!

Tickets are $100 and include entertainment, dinner, non alcoholic beverages and dessert.  There will also be a cash bar serving top shelf alcohol, beer and wine.

We have sponsorship opportunities for those of you close to Mr Kaplan wanting to make a larger impact in creating a successful event.  To become an event sponsor, simply choose the "Event Sponsor" ticket for $1500 and receive 10 tickets as well as honorable mention in all of our promotional materials and in person at the event.   Once ticket is purchased, we will be in touch to gather information to include in the program and on the event site.

Thank you to our initial Event Sponsors:

FMBK Law

Equinox, West LA

Oliver Cafe & Lounge





About Claire's Place Foundation

Claire Wineland, our foundation’s namesake, is a 19 year old girl who has been living with cystic fibrosis her entire life. She is inspired, passionate, and very excited about making a difference for other children and teens by sharing her experience, strength and hope with them. Claire has recently suffered many setbacks but maintains a positive attitude and believes this is the key to living a fulfilling life - despite being burdened with such a deadly disease.

In honor of Claire’s experience and enthusiasm for life, we created Claire’s Place Foundation, Inc., a charity committed to providing heartfelt help to families affected by Cystic Fibrosis. Our mission is to heighten public awareness about Cystic Fibrosis and improve the quality of life for the families it affects by providing education, grants, life skills, inspiration, and positive support. www.clairesplacefoundation.org

title: Voices 4 Oceans Benefit for the 5 Gyres Institute
description:
Notable actors and activists will join forces this spring to support The 5 Gyres Institute at the Voices 4 Oceans benefit storytelling event in Santa Monica, CA. Storytellers at the “Tall Tales & Silver Linings” themed event include Ashlan Gorse Cousteau (E! Entertainment), Danni Washington (“After Earth”), Eric Balfour (“Haven”), youth activist Erin Schrode, Graham Hamilton (“Code Black”), comedian Jake Johanssen, author Jillian Lauren, environmental activists Jordan Howard and Lindsay Dahl, Shiva Rose (“Return to Babylon”), Steve Connell (“We Are the Lions”), and designer/entrepreneur Steve Glenn, with surprise guests expected.

Voices 4 Oceans will take place at the beautiful Moss Theater on March 23rd. In addition to the live program, there will be a reception with an open bar, light appetizers and a silent auction. VIP guests will enjoy assigned seating and an exclusive backstage meet-and-greet with our storytellers.

All proceeds will support the 5 Gyres mission to end the global health crisis of plastic pollution, because:

300 million tons of new plastic is produced in the United States each year and less than 10 percent of plastic is recovered for recycling.
	

5.25 trillion particles weighing in at 270,000 tons of “plastic smog” pollute our oceans worldwide—and a full 80% of that marine plastic pollution comes from land.
	

More than 600 species are endangered or killed by marine plastic pollution.
	

Plastic wreaks havoc on a marine ecosystem dependent on phytoplankton, which produce 70% of the earth’s oxygen and sequester 40% of its carbon.
	

A tiny piece of plastic can be one million times more toxic than the water around it.
	

Fish are eating these microplastics—and we’re eating the fish.

        We've been fighting plastic ocean pollution since 2009, when 5 Gyres began a series of scientific firsts by researching plastic in all five subtropical gyres, as well as the Great Lakes and Antarctica. In 2014, the organization convened eight scientists around the world to publish the first Global Estimate of Marine Plastic Pollution. Our paper on plastic microbead pollution in the Great Lakes inspired a two-year collaborative campaign that culminated in a federal ban, which President Obama signed into law in 2015. This year, we're taking on polystyrene, while continuing to inspire activism through our art, education, science and adventure programs.

Thank you to our sponsors Costa, Gold Frame Media, Klean Kanteen, Life Without Plastic, Manduka, Outerknown, Reed's, and The Refill Shoppe.

title: Desert Hearts Festival 2017- Tickets On Sale Now!
description:
TICKETS ON SALE: DECEMBER 6TH @ NOON PST!
www.desertheartsfestival.com

21+ 

Hello Desert Hearts Family!

Wow it's good to be back! I think we can all agree that 2016 was one of the craziest years ever, but it's during this adversity that our Love Movement really shines brightest. The world needs love more than anything else right now and it's been our intention since day one to create as much love and positive energy as possible. We hope you'll join us once again at Los Coyotes Indian Reservation, CA on March 31st - April 3rd for our finest Desert Hearts Festival yet. We've been charging up and we're ready to blow your minds.

There's a reason the mantra of our movement is "House, Techno, & Love... We Are All Desert Hearts." Every single person who attends Desert Hearts is part of our family. A collective consciousness that we tap into together to create the ultimate vibe. Whether you're contributing a theme camp, workshop, your art, or even just a smile, the more you put in the more you get out. When we all go into Desert Hearts with the exact same intention of creating the most amount of love and positive energy possible, we're able to create a tangible vibe that sets the groundwork for the entire weekend. Vibe is king at Desert Hearts, so bring your A-Game, because we’re all bringing ours.

House, Techno, & Love… We Are All Desert Hearts. ♥

Love Always,

Your Desert Hearts Crew

~ ♥ Admission ♥ ~

Gates open for General Admission, Friday at 10am. Thursday early arrival passes allow admission Thursday at Noon. Music starts at Noon on Friday and bumps nonstop until Monday at 4pm. Tickets include entrance, camping, and access to all open kitchens, theme camps, & art installations. 

For fastest entry, please print and bring your ticket that will be emailed to you upon purchase. If you can't find the email please check your spam or promotions folder. 

* In order to encourage carpooling, an Environmental Impact Fee of $20 will be charged per vehicle. This is intended to greatly help us reduce the amount of traffic entering and exiting the festival grounds. *



♥ Tickets ♥

General Admission - $200 
Early Entry - $60 (Need to also buy a General Admission ticket)
Car Camping Pass - $80
RV Camping Pass - $165


♥ Car Camping, RV Passes, & Early Entry Passes ♥

If you are planning to camp in the campgrounds with your vehicle, you will need a Car Camping Pass. If you are arriving in a RV or bus, you will need a RV pass or else you will not be allowed entry. If you don't need to camp directly next to your car, there is a huge parking lot about a 2-5 minute walk to the campgrounds where you'll be able to park and leave your car. It is literally the shortest festival walk you'll ever do so don't even trip when Car Camping Passes sell out.

Early Entry Passes allow entrance to the festival grounds on Thursday before music starts on Friday. If you would like to enter on Thursday you will still need a regular general admission pass as well.

*Note: All cars & RVs will have to pay the standard $20 Environmental Impact Fee upon arrival, even if you bought a Car or RV Camping Pass. 


~ ♥ About Desert Hearts ♥ ~

Over the past 4 years, the Desert Hearts Family has found itself at the center of a dusty movement, fostering intimate experiences of sonic joy and unbounded love across the globe. Part boutique festival, part record label, and part globetrotting party brigade, this ragtag crew of dreamers has emerged as a vibe-focused force radiating a conscious ethos of House, Techno and Love. 

In November 2012, Desert Hearts began as a 200-person renegade gathering deep in the Mojave Desert, dreamt up by the DH’s founding quintet of Mikey Lion, Lee Reynolds, Porkchop, Marbs, & Kristoff McKay. The intrepid crew barely survived a set of extreme weather conditions and unfortunate circumstances, but that first party sparked a fire. 

In just a few short years what began as a nomadic gathering of friends, has evolved into the darling of the West Coast house and techno scene. Though each edition of the festival may sell out, the DH Crew made the decision to keep the events intimate, ensuring that the love, radical self-expression and positive energy of that first adventure remains at its beating heart. It’s what has attracted world-class bookings like Tiefschwarz, DJ Harvey, Monkey Safari, Rodriguez Jr., DJ T, Claude VonStroke, Marc Houle, Olivier Giacomotto, Mark Henning, M.A.N.D.Y, and many more.

2014 saw the launch of Desert Hearts Records, a totally-free record label embodying the musical sensibility of the movement, while providing a platform to foster established and emerging talent from around the world. Entirely curated by Mikey Lion with Marbs handling the artwork for the label, past releases have included Andreas Henneberg, Latmun, The Glitz, jozif, TÅCHES, Dance Spirit, Fritz Carlton, Kevin Anderson, RYBO, and of course records from the core Desert Hearts Crew.

The beating heart of Desert Hearts is its founding fathers. A suitably colorful cast of characters, who fell into each other's lives skating and surfing around the beaches of San Diego. Led by top hat sporting label boss Mikey Lion, the core crew is rounded out by ex-pro BMX legend turned DJ, Lee Reynolds, the artistic backbone of the crew, Marbs, Mikey’s younger brother & absolute madman, Porkchop, and renegade visionary Kristoff McKay.

If the Desert Hearts festival is the epicenter of this movement and the record label its voice, then the roaming City Hearts party series has become the legs that carry this evangelistic cause around the country. A roaming urban distillation of the festival, City Hearts has been sprinkling a little bit of California magic dust across the country and beyond, winning hearts and minds and selling out shows in Los Angeles, New York, Tulum, Mexico City, Miami, San Francisco, Houston, Chicago, Toronto, Denver, and more with more massive showings on the horizon.

Desert Hearts has given rise to a family of tens of thousands and it's safe to say the Love Movement isn’t slowing down anytime soon. Everyone that attends our events is part of our family and who are what makes the tangibly delicious vibe so astronomically good. There is no Desert Hearts without the Family.

HOUSE, TECHNO, & LOVE… WE ARE ALL DESERT HEARTS.


~ ♥ Location & Weather ♥ ~

https://www.desertheartsfestival.com/pages/directions

The Los Coyotes Indian Reservation is truly a gem to behold. Tucked in to the mountains surrounding Warner Springs (San Diego County), it brings the best of the high desert and forest together all in one. Trust us when we say we don’t know of a more beautiful place in Southern California to host our festival.

Temperatures can range from the 70s in the day to the 30s at night. Be prepared for extreme heat and cold. There are plenty of open spaces as well as ample areas shaded by trees.

There will be plenty of parking that is reasonably close to all camping areas. If you wish to bring an RV, you must purchase a pass in advance. If you would like to camp with your car, you must purchase a pass in advance.

The campground is rustic so there are no showers or functional bathrooms. We will be providing ample portapotties that will be spread throughout the venue.

* * There will be no drinking water supplies, so please bring enough to last you as well as extra to share. * *



~ ♥ Musical Offerings ♥ ~

TBA ~ but you know it’s gonna be dope baby!


~ ♥ DesertARTS ♥ ~

DH Arts Program aka DesertARTS was founded to provide a structured management platform for the involvement of community based artists and performers to create a truly unique atmosphere embedded with artistic participation and imagination. 

Art and dance are the ultimate form of self expression and it is through these platforms that we celebrate all that make us human. With the growth of Desert Hearts we have continued to focus on the expansion of our arts and outreach for community participation. We have fully committed to hosting a wide variety of artists, which include but not limited to, live painting, face/body painting, displayed art, interactive art, art installations and performance art.

For Questions, please email art@deserthearts.us


~ ♥ Yoga and Healing Sanctuary ♥ ~

Being a boutique festival that's focused so heavily on the music and vibe, we at Desert Hearts are now more than ever committed to creating space for community healers to gather and share their knowledge. Our village this year will feature healing domes from Sacred Spaces, Wet Dreams, Earthing Tea and more. Shane Chunephisal (shanechunephisal@gmail.com) has taken lead of organizing and managing our yoga and healing coordination. We will be hosting various forms of healing included but not limited to Yoga, Workshops, Sound Healing, Crystal Healing, Reiki, Energy Work, Spoken Word and Relax/Recharge Zones.

For Questions, please email workshops@deserthearts.us

~ ♥ Vendors ♥ ~ 

For Questions, please email vendors@deserthearts.us


~ ♥ Ride Share Group ♥ ~

Join our Ride Share group to find a ride or find riders to Desert Hearts. Please only make posts related to ride shares on this group.

Facebook Group:
http://bit.ly/DHRideShare


~ ♥ Creative Participation ♥ ~

Any creative energy you can bring to the gathering please do! Have some cool deco for your camp? Have some tripped out clothes or costumes? Have any paintings or art sculptures? Like to dance like never seen before? Well this is the place to do it! Let you're creative genius flourish because that is what makes us so beautiful and unique. 


~ ♥ Rules and Regulations ♥ ~

We are an open community where you can experience freedom in many ways however we have a few rules you must follow when attending Desert Hearts:

~ ABSOLUTELY NO ILLEGAL SUBSTANCES OR ILLEGAL BEHAVIOR OF ANY KIND. Including NOS tanks, balloons or any kind of drug use. Desert Hearts has a strict Zero Tolerance policy. You will be asked to leave if you violate this.

~ 21 & Up Event; ID's will be checked at the gate.

~ No re-entry if you leave the festival. Bring enough water and ice to last you throughout the weekend--they will not be sold or provided on grounds.

~ No dogs (service dogs excluded, but must be identified and leashed).

~ No renegade sound systems--basically anything larger than a small speaker. One stage, one vibe has always been our policy.

~ No littering, especially be mindful of bottles and cigarette butts. Do your part to help clean up trash when you see it.

~ Pack it in and pack it out please!!! When you leave trash at the campgrounds it puts a lot of strain on our volunteer team.


~ ♥ Leave No Trace ♥ ~

This is a leave no trace event. Pack it in, pack it out. Please do not leave your trash bags with us.

PLEASE do not leave any bottles or trash by the dance floor/speakers. If you see trash or bottles out on the ground or left out, please help clean it up and keep our land beautiful. There will be recycling containers by the stage.

It's a good idea to bring two trash bags, one for trash and one for recycling. Please pocket your cigarette butts and pick up any butts if you see them on the ground. No glow sticks or glow sand please! Also, please no feather boas or anything that will create MOOP.


~ ♥ Safety and Security ♥ ~

Desert Hearts will be staffed with a fully licensed and insured security team at all times. This does not mean you should leave your car unlocked or personal belongings out in the open. Desert Hearts is not responsible for anything that is lost or stolen.

At all our outdoor gatherings there will be a trained medical staff on standby during the entire duration of the event. If you have any medical needs please find the medic tent and they will be more than happy to service you. Please be cautious of any known allergies, illnesses, or infections you may have. Also, be cautious of your surroundings, some of our locations are known to have such things as poison oak.


~ ♥ Stay Connected ♥ ~

Website:
http://desertheartsfestival.com

Desert Hearts Records on Soundcloud:
https://soundcloud.com/desert-hearts-records

Desert Hearts On Facebook:
http://www.facebook.com/WeAreDesertHearts

Instagram:
http://instagram.com/DesertHeartsFestival
@DesertHeartsFestival 

Twitter:
https://twitter.com/DesertHearts
@DesertHearts



House ♥ Techno ♥ Love 

Infinite Love and Nonstop Beats

∞ ♥ ∞

More Info:
www.desertheartsfestival.com

title: Muddy Muggle SoCal
description:
Introducing the world’s FIRST obstacle course race inspired by the world of Harry PotterTM !

Join all of your mud-covered muggle friends as they navigate their way over obstacles that only a witch or wizard worth their wand would know how to overcome…fire-burning cauldrons, walls that appear to be 9 ¾ feet tall, quidditch quaffles flying through the air…all while being chased by demented dementors!  The 5k (3.1 mile) course is comprised of 12 wizarding obstacles to defeat, some of which may require a helping wand from a fellow witch or wizard. This is it. THIS is what you’ve been waiting for. Register today to secure your spot in what we anticipate will be a sold-out event!

THIS IS AN IMMERSIVE EXPERIENCE.

The Muddy Muggle is SO much more than just a 5k obstacle course race. Our magical gates open on the afternoon of Friday, July 14, 2017 to kick off the weekend festivities with live entertainment by Wizard Wrock bands and exciting Wizard Games in the festival village. Saturday is a FULL day of enchanting experiences beginning with the Muddy Muggle obstacle course race inspired by the world of Harry Potter. Spectators/festival goers can cheer on their favorite muggle from the sideline or spend the day browsing the shops on Horizontal Alley, participating in the numerous events and activities in Hogsbreath Hollow’s village square, or watching their favorite teams compete on the quidditch green. The choice is yours. On Saturday evening, you’ll want to come dressed to impress in your wizard best and join us for our Wizard Wrockfest and enjoy a mug of butterbeer. For those of you holding the “Prefect Pass,” you’ll join us under a canopy of stars for the Fantastic Feast, a seat-limited “farm to fork” feast filled with fresh locally, sourced flavorful faire.

As if things couldn’t possibly get any better, all Muddy Muggle participants also receive an event t-shirt, a finisher’s medal, free festival entry, and a mug of butterbeer (21 and older)!

Not just another obstacle course race! The Muddy Muggle is an immersive experience that puts YOU right in the heart of the action in our very own Hogsbreath Hollow!! Held over the course of one magical weekend, our festival gates open on the afternoon of Friday, July 14, 2017 to kick off the weekend festivities with live entertainment by Wizard Wrock bands and exciting Wizard Games in the festival village along the streets of Horizontal Alley. Saturday, July 15, 2017 offers a FULL day of enchanting experiences beginning with the Muddy Muggle obstacle course race inspired by the world of Harry Potter. Spectators/festival goers can cheer on their favorite muggle from the sideline or spend the day browsing the shops (vendors) on Horizontal Alley, participating in the numerous events and activities in Hogsbreath Hollow’s village square, or watching their favorite teams compete on the quidditch green. The choice is yours. On Saturday evening, you’ll want to come dressed to impress in your wizard best and join us for our Wizard Wrockfest where you can enjoy a refreshing mug of butterbeer! For those of you holding a pass that includes the Fantastic Feast, you’ll join us under a canopy of stars a seat-limited “farm to fork” feast filled with fresh locally, sourced flavorful faire.

Horizontal Alley

Browse the “shops” along the bustling Horizontal Alley where you’ll find everything that a witch or wizard could ask for. Catch a live demonstration by one of our numerous master craftsmen/women including candle and soap making, glass blowing, blacksmithing, and wand making! In need of a new wand? Don’t forget to stop by our wand shop where the “wand chooses the wizard.” Need to hone a few of your magical skills? Participate in potions class, divination, dark arts defense, and wizard dueling!

Village Activities

Come join the fun and participate in all that our festival has to offer! Here’s a partial list of what you’ll find in our festival square!

Hay Maze
Pumpkin Chunkin Contest
Wizard Chess
House Cup Trivia Competition
Broom Races
“Whomping Willowbroom” Mechanical Broom Challenge
Costume Contest
Autumnal Soccer
Kids’ Inflatable Obstacle Course
Horcrux Hunt
Campfire Stories in Quidditch Pitch Campground
Trick-or-Treating for our young witches and wizards
Wide World of Quidditch

Calling all quidditch athletes and fans!! Join us in Quidditch Pitch Park for all things quidditch! Demonstrations, matches, and gear expo…we have it all!

-----------------------

Real Escape Game, created by SCRAP Entertainment, is a unique and interactive live puzzle event where teams solve mysteries and clues within a time limit.

You and your fellow players are heroes actually inside the story who must escape from a scenario filled with challenging puzzles and other brainteasers.

There will be multiple teams during each game, all trying to escape. Players are encouraged to communicate frequently and divide tasks efficiently in order to solve all the puzzles before time runs out.

If you are a person who likes answering riddles, solving complex puzzles, or are just looking for a good mental challenge, this event is for you!

This is NOT a maze or traditional escape room! It is a fully hosted, story-based escape event designed for puzzle fans and fans of the Zelda franchise.

title: Magnetic Fields: "50 Song Memoir" Night One: Songs 1-25
description:
“...one of indie-rock's most acclaimed figures” - LA Times

50 Song Memoir is the new album from songwriter Stephin Merritt’s beloved recording project, the Magnetic Fields. This personal album, containing fifty songs, one for each year of the artist's life, is to be released in early 2017 on Nonesuch Records.

Unlike Stephin’s previous work, the lyrics on 50 Song Memoir are nonfiction, a mix of autobiography and documentary. There is one song per year for the fifty years since 1965. Musically the sound ranges as widely and adventurously as possible, within the context of lyrics-driven music.

In concert the music will be played and sung by seven performers in a stage set featuring fifty years of artifacts both musical (vintage computers, reel-to-reel tape decks, newly invented instruments), and decorative (tiki bar, shag carpet, vintage magazines for the perusal of idle musicians). The seven performers each play seven instruments, traditional (cello, charango, clavichord) or invented in the last 50 years (Slinky guitar, Swarmatron, synthesizer).

Each performance will be a separate program, so that the whole album will be performed over two nights: 

Night One: Songs 1-25
Night Two: Songs 26-50

description:
Come and sample dozens of domestic, imported and crafted beers and sample delicious tater tot creations for your guilty dining pleasure.

Event Times: 3p-6p

* Only 2,000 GA Tickets: Includes: Beer Passport, Tater Tot Sampling.

* Only 200 VIP Tickets: Includes: Beer Passport, Tater Tot Sampling and VIP Areas.

* Only 100 Designated Driver Tickets: Includes: Tater Tot Sampling, Soda/Water Stations.

THIS EVENT WILL SELL OUT! (We have limited capacity)

This is a 21 and over event. No babies. No strollers. No Exceptions. However, you can definitely let your inner-child out during the festival and have a blast.

* This event is about Drinking Responsibly. It is not about getting wasted. We have limited the sessions to 3hrs and will be distributing alcohol in a timely manner to avoid over-consumption. We will also cut anyone off who does not appear to be drinking responsibly. We want everyone to enjoy the event and get home safely.

* Drink Passport: Every state has different laws for how much anyone can be served during any special event. For our festivals, wherever applicable, we provide all patrons a passport to use for beer sampling. You will receive a stamp from the brewery each time you sample a beer. Depending on local liquor laws, patrons will be allowed to sample up to 30 options during the 3-hour session. Certain venues may have different requirements for this as well, and if so, will be posted on the event page of the particular event to let you know. We reserve the right to cut anyone off for any reason whatsoever.

title: Teacher Training: Container Gardening Basics
description:
Our Grow Your Own! teacher trainings equip garden educators and leaders with hands-on tools, resources, and exciting lesson plans to incorporate garden education into the classroom.

Thursday, April 20th, 2016, 3:30 to 5:00 PM at The Ecology Center!

This workshop covers the basics of growing your garden in containers. Topics covered in this 1.5 hour training session include:

Building an Herb Spiral: Design and choosing the right herbs.

Vertical Gardens: easy solutions for any school garden.

Fruit/Veggie Harvesting Guide: how to plan your harvest.

Tips for Summer Maintenance: how to keep your garden healthy with limited maintenance.

Interested in learning more about our Grow Your Own! program? Join a growing movement and engage in a hands-on teacher training experience. title: Edible & Medicinal Plants of Los Angeles County: Herb Walk
description:
EDIBLE & MEDICINAL PLANTS OF LOS ANGELES COUNTY: Seasonal Herb Walk (Spring Session)

From the wind swept coastal bluffs along the Pacific Ocean to the arid, high elevation mountain peaks of its north eastern border, the Los Angeles County region provides us with the opportunity to view a large variety of botanical specimens all within a relatively small geographical range. Join us as we discover together the diverse array of both edible and medicinal plants found growing within these contrasting yet closely interconnected plant communities. Historical and modern medicinal applications will be covered along with any edible and/or utilitarian potential. title: Flajflaj 2017
description:
Welcome to Flajflaj 2017!
(19/3 - 31/3 2017 @ Skydive Elsinore (CA))

Anyone with a skydiving A license or higher is welcome to participate, train and share the love with us at our ten year aniversary edition of this event, Flajflaj 2017!

What is Flajflaj?

Flajflaj is a series of freefly skills camps created to deliver the highest quality environment possible for skydivers on every level to develop their skills in a safe, fun and structured manner. It does not matter if you are a high level freeflyer with thousands of jumps, or if you have just received your A-license and are looking for the best way to learn solid freefly & skydiving fundamentals, Flajflaj is a camp for you!

The foundation of Flajflaj is a very high coach to student ratio. This makes it possible for the coaches to give a lot of attention to each individual participant, ensuring that no one gets left behind. We also have full time staff on the ground who are making sure that you are always in the group best suited for your needs. This is NOT a boogie where you have to lurk around to find people or organizers to jump with!! We always have great canopy coaches on staff, to make sure we never lose focus on this very important aspect of skydiving.

As always Flajflaj will take place at skydive Elsinore and we will jump from their two twin otters and two Cessna caravans (plus the occasional balloon:). The camp runs Mondays through Fridays (first Sunday evening has the opening meeting at the DZ) and most people take the weekend off to rest and do some sight seeing in California. If you´d rather stay at the DZ and get more jumps in you are more than welcome to do so. Flajflaj is made to be flexible and we always try to listen to what the participants want to do. If you want to take a break you take a break, if you want to go hard you go hard. It´s your training camp and you spend it the way you want to, but we are always there to help you progress.


Coaches, pricing, package and registration:

We are in the process of signing up coaches and this will take some time to finalize. As always we will have a spectacular lineup of coaches eager to share their knowledge and love for flying. 

We are very happy to announce this short first line up:

Alex Ranström
Ana Aponte
BJ Michaeli
Claudio Cagnasso
Daniel Croft
Domitille ”Domi” Kiger
Fabian ”Ramsy” Ramseyer

Chris Stewart (Canopy flying)
Johan Karlsson (Canopy flying)
Rob Heron (Wingsuit coaching)

Many many more coaches will ba announced soon
Stay tuned :-)

Also ready to serve us are

Carolina Mallwitz (Group coordinator extraordinaire)
Daniella Martin (Manifest wiz.)
Tomas Almbo (Video editing)

Marie Sjödin. marie@flajflaj.com
Marius Sotberg. marius@flajflaj.com
Peter Nilsson. Peter@flajflaj.com



The price of Flajflaj is divided in two payments in two currencies and for 2017 it is set to: 2260 usd AND 6950 sek. 

(As I am writing this, the total price of Flajflaj in one currency is around 3040 USD, this may vary slightly with the changing exchange rate)

This fee gets you:

Everything that is Flajflaj, including (but not limited to)
-50 jump tickets (& a discounted rate for additional jump tickets (23USD))
-Access to all the coaching & organizing (minimum 10 one on one jumps during week one (if one on one jumps is what you want to do) and A LOT of organized/coached jumps during week 2 (if average group is 3-way, you get minimum 30 jumps with a coach during week 2))
-Part of a rental car during the entire camp
-Access to canopy coaching with dedicated canopy coaches
-Access to team rooms for video debriefing and gear storage
-Weekly videos (professional editing), T-shirts, Poker tournament entry (included for 2017 with lots of added prices from our sponsors) party's and the freefly experience of a life time!

The SEK fee needs to be paid within 14 days after registering to secure your slot. Please note that this part of the fee is NON REFUNDABLE. You will always be able to transfer/sell your slot to another person, but since the money will already have been spent on bringing in all the coaches etc. there will be no room for a refund from this part of the fee.

The USD sum needs to be paid before 2nd Feb 2017

Accommodation

We have a great relationship with the Lake Elsinore hotel and casino, where most of us will be staying. They offer us a discounted rate of 54USD (tax not included) per two bedded room (27USD per person and night). It´s possible to make arrangements for more people to share one room to keep costs down, but extra beds are not available.

For 2017 we will have 25 beds available in the DZ bunk house, at 10USD per night. These are available on a first come (read; sign up) first served basis.

(On the registration form you will have to state where you want to stay and in the case of bunk house or hotel accommodation, we take care of the bookings for you as always).

It is possible to put up a tent (free of charge), rent an RV, or make other arrangements of your liking.

Registration

Registration opens 1/10 for everyone who have been to Flajflaj before and one week later, 8/10 for everyone looking to join us for the first time. Slots are limited, sign up early for this big aniversary event!

To make sure you get all the info as soon as it is released; join the facebook page and send us an email (mailinglist@flajflaj.com) so we can add you to the mailinglist.

Any questions you might have please send us an email at info@flajflaj.com

Peace Love & Freeflying
/Peter :o)

PS: Extra love as always to Indoor-skydiving Bottrop, L&B, NZaerosports, option Studios, VossVind, UPT and Skydive Elsinore

description:

Step into the enchanted world of Broadway's modern classic, Disney's Beauty and the Beast, an international sensation that has played to over 35 million people worldwide in 13 countries. Based on the Academy Award-winning animated feature, the stage version includes all of the wonderful songs written by Alan Menken and the late Howard Ashman, along with new songs by Mr. Menken and Tim Rice. The original Broadway production ran for over thirteen years and was nominated for nine Tony Awards, including Best Musical.

The classic story tells of Belle, a young woman in a provincial town, and the Beast, who is really a young prince trapped under the spell of an enchantress. If the Beast can learn to love and be loved, the curse will end and he will be transformed into his former self. But time is running out. If the Beast does not learn his lesson soon, he and his household will be doomed for all eternity.

title: The Contemporary Performance Collective featuring the Lyris Quartet
description:
THE CONTEMPORARY PERFORMANCE COLLECTIVE
The CPC is dedicated to commissioning, promoting, and performing concerts of 21st-century chamber music works. Through concerts and outreach, we make music of the highest caliber accessible to every member of the community, regardless of economic circumstances.

The Lyris Quartet performs at CPC II

The LYRIS QUARTET described as "radiant…exquisite... and powerfully engaged" by Mark Swed of the LA Times was founded in 2008. Members of the quartet have won top prizes at the Tchaikovsky International Competition and Aspen Music Festival and have collaborated with renowned artists Natalia Gutman, David Geringas, Martha Argerich, Alban Gerhardt, Boris Pergamenschikov, Guillame Sutre, Myung-Whun Chung, and Richard Stoltzman.

The Lyris Quartet is the founding resident ensemble of the Hear Now Music Festival which focuses on the music of living Los Angeles composers. As part of this series, they have collaborated with and premiered works by Stephen Hartke, Don Davis, Arturo Cardélus, and Veronika Krausas, among others. The Lyris Quartet has recorded for Toccata Classics, ARS and Naxos.

They will be giving a concert at La Sierra University's Hole Memorial Auditorium on Wednesday, May 24, 2017 at 7p.

For more information about the Contemporary Performance Collective, please visit their website:

http://www.cpcmusicgroup.com/


Proceeds from this event will go towards future collaborative projects with the CPC.

Purchase your tickets online before May 24th and you will receive a discount!

IGNIGHT MOVING MEDITATIONS

FLOW: an exhilarating transcendent meditation in which effortless control & peak skills blend to erase all sense of time and space

190+ Flow Arts classes, Astronomy exhibits, Circus, Archery, Pool, Yoga classes, Flow music and a Wellness Center built by Frank Lloyd Wright will create an environment where access to mind expanding knowledge will keep you in the flow.

Join our community page for updates!

http://ignightconference.com/?page_id=105

***You're allowed to transfer your ticket(s) to other conference goers. Please report all changes to management. We will try to accommodate last minute ticket changes, but can not guarantee refunds after May, 2017. There will be a list at the gate, if your name is not on it, you will not be able to attend the conference***

Need help getting there?

https://www.facebook.com/groups/362048440502145/

If you are interested in performing in the IgNight 2017 Instructor Showcase please contact info@ignightconference.com

Flow is the state of optimal experience that occurs when your body, mind, and spirit are in dynamic balance. It's what's happening when the Now is so compelling that everything else fades away. Ego and fear dissolve in the perfect moment, time slows down, and whatever you're doing becomes a meditation. Flow toes the fine line between controlling your actions and obeying your commands. You know when you're in the flow, and flowing is half the battle. Where will and physics intersect, we hone our own flow.

Thank you for all your support and patronage. Because of your involvement, IgNight has grown from a collective dream into a full blown reality. The San Bernardino Fire Marshals, the Joshua Tree Sheriff department and the Joshua Tree Chamber of Commerce appreciate and welcome our community gathering. They invite us to keep on teaching, learning and sharing our skills up in Joshua Tree.

title: Greywater Systems for the Home
description:
Upcycle water at home by installing a simple laundry-to-landscape greywater system!

The average four person household sends over 38,000 gallons of reusable water down the drain each year from bathrooms and laundries. With a greywater system, you can divert this water into the garden instead of down the drain.

One of the easiest systems to install is a Laundry-to-Landscape greywater system. This system benefits your home, garden, community, local ecology and ecosystems, and your wallet. Once installed, it helps conserve and reuse good water everyday, without having to think about it.

Some benefits of a Laundry-to-Landscape system are:


	Reduced water consumption (lower water bills)
	Free water to feed your garden
	Reduced pollution on local watersheds and the ocean
	Reduced energy needs at your local water treatment plant

Join us to learn how to be a part of the solution with a simple greywater system. In this workshop we will:


	Learn about the difference between clear water, greywater, and blackwater
	Explore a few simple and common types of home greywater systems
	Learn how to build a Laundry-to-Landscape system step-by-step
	Mock-up a Laundry-to-Landscape & Branched Drain system with real parts

This workshop will provide you with the basic knowledge and hands on instructions on how to install a Laundry-to-Landscape & Branched Drain greywater system for your home. All attendees will receive informational hand-outs to complement the subjects covered in the workshop and free Dr. Bronner's biodegradable soap samples.

INSTRUCTOR BIO
Ty Teissere specializes in backyard orchard care, from building the soil life to pruning the canopy, and the irrigation systems in between. He has taught ecological workshops on permaculture design, greywater, earthen construction, fermentation, and kids classes on making compost with worms. Ty is based in Pomona and is a certified arborist (#WE-10547-A), greywater installer (Greywater Action), rainwater harvester (Watershed Management Group), and has his horticulture certificate from Long Beach City College.

title: Sigur Rós - Walt Disney Concert Hall (April 13th)
description:
http://sigur-ros.co.uk/tour/2017/20170413-rvk-fest-1/

The Los Angeles Philharmonic have announced that programming for their Reykjavík Festival will include three special shows by Sigur Rós performing some of their best loved works with the orchestra. This is the first time the band will have played publicly with an orchestra since shows for their unreleased work Odin’s Raven Magic in 2002-3. 

Co-curated by Icelandic composer Daníel Bjarnason and LA Phil Conductor Laureate Esa-Pekka Salonen, the Icelandic band will perform three nights at Walt Disney Concert Hall, playing career-spanning sets including fan-favorites (with orchestral accompaniment) and - “if things go to plan” - new, unreleased music (without orchestra).

Each Sigur Rós performance (April 13, 14, 15) will be prefaced by a different symphonic and choral program. On April 13 festival co-curator Salonen will lead the LA Phil in the world premier of a new violin concerto from Daníel Bjarnason, performed by Pekka Kuusisto.  Bjarnarson first worked with Sigur Rós when he conducted the session on the band’s song “Ára Bátur” London’s Abbey Road for the Með suð í eyrum… album in 2008.

The April 13, 14, 15 programs will also include new work from long-term Sigur Rós collaborator and Amiina member Maria Huld Markan Sigfúsdóttir, as well as pieces from Anna Þorvaldsdóttir and Jón Leifs. In addition, the orchestra will also present the U.S. premieres of Haukur Tómasson’s piano concerto, with Icelandic soloist Vikingur Ólafsson, and Hlynur Aðils Vilmarsson’s BD. (see full schedule below)

The Reykjavík Festival is designed as an exploration of the eclectic Icelandic music scene, highlighting the creativity thriving in Reykjavík and covering a wide spectrum of music, from chamber, choral and symphonic to pop music.

title: Un-Private Collection: Tony Conrad: Completely in the Present
description:
The Broad is pleased to present the West Coast premiere of Tyler Hubby’s documentary film, Tony Conrad: Completely in the Present. The film examines the pioneering life and work of artist, musician, and educator, Tony Conrad, and this special iteration of The Un-Private Collection series highlights both his extraordinary career and his influence on the work of Broad collection artists including Mike Kelley, Robert Longo, and Tony Oursler. Since the early 1960s, Conrad's vast, inter-disciplinary repertoire has created and influenced major film and compositional movements. He performed in and recorded the soundtrack to Jack Smith’s legendary film Flaming Creatures; he defied conventions of cinema with The Flicker, an experimental structuralist film composed of a precise pattern of alternating black and white frames; he developed and practiced Just Intonation and Minimalism with Karlheinz Stockhausen and La Monte Young; and he was instrumental in the formation of The Velvet Underground. 

A post-screening conversation with Tyler Hubby and Tony Oursler will be moderated by Henry Rollins. Iconic artist and musician, Kim Gordon, who has collaborated with Tony Conrad, will perform to close out the night. Works by Tony Oursler in the Broad collection are currently on view in the collection installation, Creature, through March 19.

Bring your ticket for this program to The Broad and skip the line for general admission entry without advance reservation between March 14 - 19.

title: Backyard Orchard Design & Care
description:
Learn how to cultivate an abundant, healthy backyard orchard perfect for our local climate.

Southern California’s mild climate is well suited to grow a variety of different fruit trees, yielding bushels of organic, delicious produce right in your own backyard. With just a few well-adapted trees and some simple principles of ecological design, you'll have an abundant orchard in no time.

A home orchard has many benefits, including:


	Fresh, organic fruit (15-30 lbs per tree, every season)
	Mulch and shade for your garden (reducing water evaporation and irrigation) and cooling for your home (energy savings)
	Absorption of CO2 and harmful air pollutants, production of oxygen
	Habitat for beneficial native birds, insects and animals
	Improved soil water retention
	Less dependency on grocery stores, creating savings and independence

With the right tools and knowledge, an ecological orchard is simple to start, establish, and maintain.

Join us in this workshop to learn how. Together we will:


	Learn how to design an ecological backyard orchard
	Learn step-by-step how to start, establish, and maintain a backyard orchard
	Discuss the fruit tree selection, site preparation, planting, irrigation, pruning, natural pest control, and other techniques to maintain a healthy orchard
	Observe a diverse fruit tree orchard in action at The Ecology Center

All attendees will receive informational hand-outs to complement the subjects covered in the workshop, and take home their own FREE small starter fruit tree!

description:
The Poetry Brothel is a unique and immersive poetry event that takes poetry outside classrooms and lecture halls and places it in the lush interiors of a bordello. The Poetry Brothel presents a rotating cast of both male and female poets as “whores,” each operating within a carefully crafted character, who impart their work in public readings, spontaneous eruptions of poetry, and most distinctly, as purveyors of private poetry readings on beds, chaise lounges and in private rooms. For a small fee, all of the “poetry whores” are available for these sequestered readings at any time during the event. Of course, any true brothel needs a good cover; The Poetry Brothel’s is an immersive cabaret, offering a full bar, musicians, burlesque dancers, painters, actors, and fortune-tellers, with newly integrated themes, performances and installations at each event.

title: Bubble RUN Anaheim 2017!
description:
How does this all go down? 
Super simple!
Clad in white t-shirts, Participants run, walk, dance and play across 5 Kilometers (3.1 miles) of absolute fun! Waves start every 3-5 minutes, then at each kilometer participants will run through the Bubble Bogs where there is enough colored foam to cover you from head to toe!
Each of the four Bubble Bogs along the course are represented by different colored foam for you to frolic through!
We're all about maximum fun, and with that comes a few simple rules: 
Rule 1: All levels of runners, walkers, twirlers, dancers and strollers are welcome to the Bubble Run™, but follow the announcer's instructions at all times!
Rule 2: Wear white for maximum (washable) color exposure!
Rule 3: Enjoy being a kid again!

title: KINGDOM HEARTS Orchestra - World Tour - (Los Angeles)
description:
From Hollywood to Westminster, from the Champs Elysée to the Marunouchi, the first official symphonic concert of Kingdom Hearts is set to enchant the world starting March 10, 2017 in Tokyo. Uniting the worlds and characters of FINAL FANTASY and Disney to create a brand new thrilling mythology, Kingdom Hearts follows the adventures of Sora, Goofy and Donald as they rescue their friends and the whole world. With two major games, Kingdom Hearts I and II, released on PlayStation 2 (and re-released in HD on PlayStation 3), and six spin off games over multiple platforms, the saga has touched millions of fans around the globe.

World class professional orchestra, such as the Royal Philarmonic Orchestra in London and the Tokyo Philarmonic Orchestra in Japan, will perform a selection of the best and most beloved music from the original soundtrack of the whole saga.  The concert will feature more than 70 musicians on stage, with amazing HD video cinematics supervised by director Testuya Nomura himself. It will premiere in Tokyo on 10, 2017, and tour the world henceforth. The long awaited official orchestral concert is about to start, so prepare to unleash again the power of the Keyblades and don’t miss this new adventure and experience!

Available on May 14, 2016 at www.ticketmaster.com

title: Rhythm of  Earth II - Ken Koshio and KENZOO with Special Guest, TAKERU
description:
Rhythm of the Earth IIKen Koshio and KENZOOwith Special Guest, TAKERU (former YAMATO performer)

Powerful Taiko beats resonate with your heartbeat“Ryhthm of the Earth”- produced and performed by Ken Koshio, KENZOO and special guest from Japan: TAKERU - echoes with a sound that could only come from soulful and powerful spirits, which resonate your heartbeat, and connects people across cultures and to our planet.

Ken Koshio is a world class Japanese Taiko drummer. He produced many cultural events and concerts, especially Taiko ‘n’ Roll Live Show, which has been very successful. Taiko is a Japanese style of percussion, combining music, movement and spirit. Ken pushes the boundaries of Taiko through various collaborations, creating a totally authentic and unique style of music. It is truly an amazing and powerful production and exciting performance you will see with an amazing special guest TAKERU.

Advance Concert Tickets$20 Adult/$10 Student

TIckets at Door$25 Adult/$15 Student

Special rate for person who attend the workshopAdult:Workshop $20/Concert: $10: Bundle $30Concert: $10

Students:Workshop $15/Concert $5: Bundle $20

TAKERU:In 1995 Takeru joined Yamato one of the major professional Taiko groups in Japan. Yamato was founded in 1993 in Japan’s Nara Prefecture. He was an outstanding performer and played a main role for Yamato, and has given over 2,500 performances in 51 countries and regions. In 2016 he retired from Yamato and is currently performing as a solo artist and collaborating with many talented artist in continuing his career to create his passions in life. He continues to perform throughout Japan and around the world to spread the spirit of Japan.

title: FDR Beer Appreciation 101
description:
Ever wanted to know more about beer but were too intimidated to ask? Don’t know the difference between a Saison and a Stout, but not sure who to turn to? Are you a connoisseur of craft beer, but are always looking to learn more about what goes into giving beer it’s multitude of different aromas, flavors, and colors? Then look no further, we’ve got the event for you!

Come learn from Kevin, our Head Brewer and Nationally-ranked Beer Judge, and sample EIGHT beers, as he gives an overview of the ingredients that provide beers their unique characteristics, discusses what defines various brewing cultures and centers around the world, and highlights numerous beer styles and what makes them similar and different from one another. Throughout the discussion, you’ll gain an appreciation for why you may like certain beers, while understanding why you may not enjoy others quite so much. You’ll also enjoy a tour of our brewery and an overview of the complete Ferment.Drink.Repeat brewing process.

The knowledge you’ll gain in our Beer Appreciation 101 Class will help you make better-informed beer style selections in the future and is a perfect way to start off your SF Beer Week adventure!

title: NO DAKOTA ACCESS PIPELINE - SACRAMENTO
description:
Current Updates; NODAPL SACRAMENTO and CAPSITY is hosting a NYE Solidarity Party in the name of STANDING ROCK. Tickets are in the above section, purchase yours today and RSVP for the party before the space fills up!




Hello y'all, thank you so much for donating to demand justice. We are in solidarity with thousands of First Nation Peoples and Billions of people across the world resisting choices not representing the public. The Dakota Access Pipeline, Oceti Sakowin prayer gatherings, and mass bank divestment, are microcosms of systemic corruption. This stand for indigenous justice echos many other stands for justice, human rights violations whether it be chemically infused freezing water from a water cannon or a conviction less homicide from a fire arm. Black Lives Matter.

 #sayhername

These systemic issues effect the entirety of the planet, please understand donating what you think you can afford isn’t enough  anymore. We must rise up and answer those that have committed their immediate existence to change, remember, we all feel the momentum, now we must act.

We have an opportunity to show how Sacramento stands with Standing Rock, we are dedicated to adverting any further construction of the Dakota Access Pipeline; or any other pipeline for that matter, we see you Texas. Please Share This if you or anyone you know is willing to travel to Support the Future of fresh water and the well-being of the Earth! We will only be able to take those whom are openly willing to practice radical self-inclusion and radical listening, these are not request as much as initial initiation to the cultural space. So, please if you want to use your body in support bring your friends, AS A REQUIREMENT NATIVE FRIENDS FIRST PLEASE!

It is an extremely cold winter in North Dakota. Period.

The water protectors are going to sleep cold and waking up cold, we know this! The current direction at hand is fundraising, this moment fundraising to provide basic survival requirements; medical supplies, extreme cold weather living structures, in state fire wood. The team orchestrating this symphony of ride shares and money delegations are a delegation comprised of concerned community champions. We decided that If veterans can raise a million dollars so can we, the community of Sacramento! Sí se puede! Sí se puede! Sí se puede!

We have meeting every two weeks in the midtown area of Sacramento. Like the NoDAPL Sacramento Facebook page to follow the status of Standing Rock, and send a message to the page we will get in contact with you!

Mni Wiconi

title: The Essence of Balance: A Day of Yoga and Wine at Big Basin Vineyards
description:
What does "balance" mean to you? Prepare to start the day finding your inner balance with a centering yoga flow class. From there, you will step off the mat and out into Big Basin's estate vineyard in the beautiful Santa Cruz Mountains, where you will witness firsthand how organic and Biodynamic grape growing nurture and sustain the delicate balance of nature's energies. Finally, you will sit down to an in-depth Sommelier-guided wine tasting and lunch, during which you will learn how to identify the basic elements of balance in wine using the power of your own senses and intuition. No yoga or wine experience needed. Just an open mind and willingness to explore! 


	10:30am - Meet and greet at the winery
	11am - 12pm:  Yoga class
	12pm -1:30 Vineyard and winery tour 
	1:30-3pm - Sit-down tasting and lunch

Cost of the workshop: $100 per person

EARLYBIRD 20% off tickets now available thru midnight 03/01/17! Select EARLYBIRD at the ticket menu!

Your Guides: 

Gizella Donald, ERYT, Studio Director & Founder, Yoga Mayu of San Francisco - Gizella is the owner of Yoga Mayu, a five start boutique yoga studio with two locations in San Francisco's most popular neighborhoods, the Mission District and Noe Valley. Gizella began her studies and practice in 1990 at the Sivananda Yoga Center in San Francisco. Since then she has practiced in different classical Yoga traditions including Ashtanga and Iyengar styles. She teaches an energetic, challenging yet playful class, and excels in modifying poses so that they can be accessible to all levels of students. She inspires her students to extend the practice of yoga by encouraging them to bring the love of yoga into their everyday life.

Bradley Brown, Founder, Winemaker, Proprietor and Vineyard Manager, Big Basin Vineyards - Bradley’s interest in wine was initially inspired by his father, Glenn, who was an avid home winemaker and Big Basin Vineyards was founded and remains a family owned and operated winery. With the guidance of Rhone Ranger John Alban, Bradley planted the Rattlesnake Rock Estate vineyard in 2000 followed by his foray into winemaking with the first vintage in 2002. A farmer first, Bradley understands the importance of vineyard site and viticultural practices and is committed to organic farming as a way to improve the expression of site; the entire Estate vineyard is Certified Organic by CCOF. Recently, Big Basin Vineyards was selected to join 32 of California’s top Pinot Noir and Chardonnay producers to be represented at In Pursuit of Balance, an organization which seeks to promote dialogue around the meaning and relevance of balance in California wine.

Chiara Rose Shannon, WSET Certified Sommelier, ERYT 500 - Chiara Rose Shannon is a sommelier, wine buyer, and yoga instructor based in California. Chiara has over ten years wine industry experience including six years at K&L Wine Merchants based in Redwood City, where she served as Head Sommelier. A native of Los Angeles, Chiara returned home in 2014 to manage one of the area's most respected neighborhood retail wine shops, Mission Wines. Chiara has been practicing yoga for over fifteen years and has been certified in yoga instruction through Yoga Tree in San Francisco and YogaWorks in Los Angeles. Through her experiences, Chiara has developed a unique understanding of the relationship between yoga and wine and seeks to share this with her students in ways that are accessible, enlightening and fun.

title: Thinking Matters Adult Learning at CBS
description:
Our popular Thinking Matters: Modern Jewish Philosophy mini-course series kicks off a new semester in September. Join our impressive line-up of local star teachers and CBS experts to wrestle with today’s urgent questions of Jewish philosophy. Can there be such a thing as a Jewish philosophy, or a philosophy of Judaism? How does Judaism relate to the broader question of the relationship of ethics, religion, and theology to philosophy? (For an introduction to Jewish modern thought and philosophy, we recommend Steven Katz’s essay, “Eliezar Berkovits & Modern Jewish Philosophy.”)

Details and readings for select upcoming Thinking Matters classes and mini-courses can be found here. The full 2016–17 mini-course overview can be accessed here.

All classes meet on Thursday evenings from 6:30 – 8 p.m.

title: The HOOTENANNY! Tour | Auburn, CA
description:
Tim & the Glory Boys are headed your way on their 2017 HOOTENANNY tour!

Tim Neufeld (also of the band “STARFIELD”) is a multiple JUNO, Dove, and Covenant award winning Christian artist based out of Abbotsford, British Columbia, Canada. He and the Glory Boys (A world-class Canadian bluegrass trio) have shared the stage on cross-Canada tours with artists such as Third Day, and most recently, his worshipfulness, Chris Tomlin. Now, starting September 2016, they’re hitting the road on their biggest headlining tour to date, bringing their ‘Worship Hoedown’ to your backyard!

What is “Worship Hoedown” you ask?

It’s a bluegrass inspired night of music and joy... beards, banjos, and blessings for the whole family! A night of corporate worship; with hymns, choruses, original songs, and comedy, geared towards all ages and denominations. It’s Baptists, Pentecostals, Catholics (and everything in between). It’s the local churches coming together to worship in unity, It’s a HOOTENANNY!

title: Mutiny Radio Comedy Festival 2017: Newbies (>2yrs)
description:
You won't believe these comics have been performing less than 2 years.  You won't believe they are all newbies to the comedy game!

Host Zane Barrett is a Bay Area comedian who is also a scientist. He experiments with cancer cells during the day then experiments with making the funny at night. His material covers everyday life scenarios and the darker side of familiar ideas.  With a little over a year in the scene he is grinding away at becoming a working comic someday.  Zane Barrett has performed at open mics all over the city (Brainwash, Purple Onion, Mutiny Radio, etc) and currently runs the amazing Bomb Shelter open mic.

Hunter Donaldson is a comedian based out of Portland, Oregon who originally hails from Fayetteville, Arkansas. He has been featured on many local Portland comedy showcases and made it to the semi-finals of the Portland Funniest Person contest. He wears sweaters and people like that and he is nice.

Geneva Rust-orta- Geneva first tried stand up comedy in 2015 at the Jewish Comedian of the Year Competition in London, where she was named ‘Second Funniest Jew’. She took a show, ‘Messed Up’, to the 2016 Camden and Edinburgh Fringe Festivals in the UK. She’s new to the Bay Area comedy scene.

I'm Tony Lewis, I am a native to the Puget Sound of Washington State. I have been doing standup for 2 years mostly in the Olympia/Tacoma Scene. I've featured at World Famous Nicks and also in Olympias Pig Bar and also at Le Voyeurs weekly Vomity Open mic. I've been on the podcasts :"Everything is Awesome" and also "The Stationwagon Podcast" as well as hosted my own "The Ye Old Olympic Comedy Hour". I used to do pre-taped sketches with my group Dorsal Fin United. I have performed also at the Olympia Hempfest and took 2nd place at the Northwest Cannabis Comedy Competition.  

Local Mike Evans Jr. Hosts Old Soul Radio a weekly podcast on Mutiny Radio Sunday nights from 10p to midnight .

title: Elk Grove Brewfest 2017
description:
ELK GROVE BREWFEST

Elk Grove Brewfest is returning for another year, and with an ever growing craft beer scene in Elk Grove, it's high time that the city had an annual Brewfest. EGBF sold out last year, so don't wait to get your tickets!

Elk Grove Brewfest will take place in Old Town Elk Grove at Old Town Plaza on Friday, May 26th, 2017 from 6-10PM.

The event is brought to you by Beers In Sac, in partnership with the City of Elk Grove, and will be benefiting Elk Grove’s own, the Runnin’ For Rhett Foundation.

Elk Grove Brewfest will feature 50+ breweries, cideries, meaderies, and a few wineries, with local gourmet food trucks, vendors, a cigar lounge, and live music and entertainment. Come and take in the sights at Historic Elk Grove and join us for a night to remember at this community focused and inspired event. Must be 21+ years old to enter.

title: Mutiny Radio Comedy Festival 2017: Who'd Ya Vote For?
description:
These political comics are going to tell it like it is!  Truth talk about our state of the Union.  Sometimes politics are so scary, all we can do is laugh!

Host Jazmyn Washington- Jazmyn W is an up and coming comedian and actress represented by The Stars Agency here in San Francisco. She performs in shows all across the bay area and has graced the stage of the Great Star Theater. You can keep an eye out for in the upcoming web series "Underwoods of Napa Valley." 

JEFF YOUNG has been performing across the country to rave reviews. His memorable cadence, dark outlook, and thoughtful material combined with his loveable and vulnerable personality, leaves audiences laughing, then scratching their heads at the disassociated absurdity of his act. Equally popular with mature and youth audiences, YOUNG takes on tough topics like family and politics, juxtaposing them with bizarre observations of pop culture and existence. Based in NYC, YOUNG has been featured on Gotham Comedy Live, The World Series of Comedy, Amateur Night at the Apollo and is a regular at clubs including The Stand in NYC, The Comedy Studio in Boston and Comedy Connection in Providence.

Joe Messina is a comic based in Philadelphia. He is a regular at Helium Comedy Club and cohosts the monthly political comedy show Party Lines at Good Good Comedy Theater. He has performed at venues throughout the country and in 2016 was featured on the Liberty Tour in Philadelphia and Denver.

Patrick Fowler- With his dark humor and dry wit, Patrick Fowler has been entertaining audiences since 2011.  His deadpan delivery and awkward stage manner makes him well-liked in people with low to medium self-esteem, focusing on topics such as life, death, and all the little things in between.  Based in South Bend, Indiana, Patrick has performed in venues all over Michigan and Indiana.  He has performed at Gilda’s Laughfest, was a semifinalist in the Funniest Person in Grand Rapids, and a manager at The Drop Comedy Club in South Bend.

Ben Quick- With a thousand-watt smile and a razor-sharp intellect, Ben Quick has a lot on his mind. Combining a wide array of talents from the rhetorical to the musical, Ben's twisted, analytical neurosis brings a high-energy point of view to the stage that’s equal parts undeniable and uncompromising.
