� STYN (Amsterdam, Netherlands)
http://www.soundcloud.com/stijn-schrijber
https://www.facebook.com/stynbeats

Styn, hailing from Netherlands, is an electronic music producer. Starting production at the age of 13, Styn is no new comer in the scene. Being influenced by the names of Pete Rock, J Dilla, 9th Wonder & Madlib, Styn only produced hip hop at first. Not wanting to limit himself to just one genre, Styn also started to produce diffrent genres. He started to produce dubstep at the age of 16. Nowadays, Styn is better known as a dubstep producer rather than a hip hop producer.

Styn continues to break down barriers between genres, regularly gaining support for his Dubstep, Trap, and various other styles of electronic music and hop hop from top industry producers including UZ, 12th Planet, Getter, Borgore, Gentelmens Club, p0gman, Bukez Finezt, Shiverz, and more! His production has seen releases on Buygore, Monsters, Arcane, and Courteous Family.

Internationally known, Styn has smashed the decks across the globe at numerous gigs in countries including France, Russia, Belgium, USA, Germany, and Czech Republic just to name a few. With a plethora of production under his belt including originals and official remixes, Styn is a major force in the Bass Music scene.

� BERRIX (Antwerp, Belgium)
https://www.facebook.com/BerrixOfficial
https://soundcloud.com/berrix

Dubstep artist from Belgium, Berrix is most known for his dj abilities & mixdowns, forging the way with his controversial technical style. “Berrix produces all sorts of Dubstep that wobbles & womps through your body, making you dance whether you want to or not.”

Berrix experienced his first love for dubstep around 2007-2008 and only started making dubstep himself in 2014, taking all sorts of styles along the way with him but keeping the hard hitting dancefloor destruction sound as his personal favorite. Berrix may only be 2 years into the game, however his signature sound has gained him tons of international support. With releases on: Full Flex Audio, Blacklight Audio, Bewildered & Dub Selection, he has been getting overall support from the likes of Shiverz, Bukez Finezt, Akira, Styn, Kahlil, Jakes, Blankface, AD, Infekt, SubFiltronik, Badphaze, BloodThinnerz, Stinkahbell and many more. Berrix signature style has quickly become a staple in the riddim dubstep scene.

The phenomenon is still growing, Berrix is becoming an upcoming legend of the dubstep scene. With an incredibly loyal fan base he's is known world wide for working hard, playing hard and DJing hard on stages globally.

title: Certified Scrum Product Owner Feb 9-10 Malvern, PA (Phila area)
description:
The CSPO® certification course focuses on functioning as the product owner, or customer, for a Scrum team. You will learn about activities such as managing stakeholders, ROI, backlog grooming, creating effective stories, acceptance criteria for stories, and defining done. This two-day certification program is taught by a Certified Scrum Trainer (CST) with over 20 years IT industry experience.

Topics covered:

Overview of Agile Methods and Definition of Scrum

Why Agile?

The Agile Manifesto

Overview of KANBAN

Roles and Responsibilities

Scrum Artifacts and Ceremonies

User Stories and Acceptance Criteria

Product and Sprint Backlog

Story Point Estimation

Definition of Readiness and Done

Dependences and Scaling Scrum

Included with your tuition: Two year membership in ScrumAlliance®

Story Point estimation cards provided

All students earn:

- Scrum Education Units (SEUs)

- Project Management Institute (PMI®) members earn PDUs

Free enrollment in ScrumAlliance® authorized AgilePA Users Group

Continental breakfast and lunch provided during class.

title: Musicale: DAVE CHAPPELLE'S BLOCK PARTY
description:
On September 18, 2004, Dave Chappelle threw a block party on the corner of Quincy and Downing streets in Brooklyn, New York. In what became something not unlike a send-off to Chappelle’s Show—which ended just months after Block Party premiered—Dave gathered the musicians he most admired, his friends and frequent collaborators from his acclaimed comedy show and Def Poetry Jam.

Featuring performances by Kanye West, Black Star’s Mos Def (Yasiin Bey) and Talib Kweli, Jill Scott, Erykah Badu, Questlove, Black Thought and The Roots crew, Common, Big Daddy Kane, Dead Prez, John Legend, and—a miracle—The Fugees, Dave Chappelle’s Block Party is a love letter to East Coast hip hop. The Michel film also features the exact moment Kanye West morphed from “College Dropout” to the Yeezus that we know and love today.

MUSICALE – (noun) a program of music performed at a party – is a monthly film series at The Royal.

Dosika: Dosika is a Dubstep and Trap producer based in the south of Scotland, bringing hard hitting beats and heavy bass, he is one to look out for!

title: Boudoir Bohème - A Sensual Soirée
description:
An immersive, sensual soirée inspired by Romanticism and Bohemians of 19th century Paris.

We invite you to a night where standard conventions and behaviors are thrown out the door, where everyone is an artist, and is free to be whoever they wish.

Have you ever wanted to escape, to get lost in a foreign land, take a new name, and indulge in the exotic?

For one night we will put on the most exotic outfits and dance with our eyes closed, paint our flesh as though it were a canvass, drip hot wax onto a living sculpture, lay on Persian rugs and lounge on bedouin throw pillows.

Boudoir Boheme is a night of immersive performances, interactive art installations, live music, dancing, and intimate interactions: careful, you might get whisked away by one of our artists to reveal your innermost desires…Join in intimate rituals, mischief, mirth, and luxuriate in a luscious atmosphere complete with all the characters from your most colorful dreams…

This is a night like you’ve never experienced before. Throw all social mores out the window and dance with a total stranger. Act like an artist from French Bohemia. Wear a mask and take a new name. Become your alter ego. Travel across oceans without ever having to leave…

Immersive Performances
Burlesque and Belly Dance
Boudoir Photo Studio
Performance Art
Kidnappings and Intimate One-on-One Interactions
Live Body Painting
Sensual Rituals
Pillow Lounge
Live Musical Performances
Roaming Performances Throughout the Night
DJs Playing Sexy World Grooves

Dress code enforced: Black tie or costume for gents, elegant or exotic attire for ladies. For costume ideas see our Pinterest board. 
http://bit.ly/PinterestBoheme

Location of venue will be sent to you 24 hours before the event.

title: SLINK 101
description: $10 8pm 2 sets Bio.Slink 101Bobby Cashman: bass guitar and backing vocalsMarc Bruck: drumsSlink Moss: vocals and guitarSlink 101 is a power pop trio formed in 2016 in Columbia County NY and has already created a buzz and dedicated following with their raucous house parties and jam sessions. Slink 101 draws from a wide range of influences like boogie woogie, southern rock, 80s goth, ska, and punk. At times sounding like The Clash, then Tom Petty, then Neil Young, then a dance band, and in then end, Slink 101 has a sound totally their own with great dynamics and catchy original tunes. Slink Moss is an accomplished song-writer and Bobby and Marc provide a perfect back-beat and unique style. It's original, it's fun, it's Slink 101!

title: Capture the Everglades Photography Workshop and Tour
description:
Come
 explore one of South Florida’s most incredible, picturesque places, The
 Everglades National Park. You will be guided by yours truly and my 
team.

You will get a chance to photograph the area like you have never seen
 it before. Escaping to my favorite places to photograph nature, 
landscapes and wildlife. Ending this incredible tour by catching an 
amazing sunset from my secret spot in all of The Everglades.

This 8 hour workshop is designed to master your photography skills 
and also to awaken your creative process. This entire workshop is hands 
on and I will be with you every step of the way covering composition, 
camera settings, chasing the light, and much more. You will see, and 
photograph the Everglades like never before.



Itinerary:

11:00am – 11:20am – Meet and Greet at Ernest Coe Visitor Center where
 you can meet everyone and get to know each other. You can also take 
this opportunity to carpool with the other photographers.

11:00pm – 1:00pm Shoot Anhinga Trail Great for wild life photos.

1:00pm – 2:00pm Surprise spot

2:00pm – 3:00pm Shoot West Lake View

3:00pm – 4:00pm Lunch (not included in workshop fee please bring your own)

4:00pm – 6:00pm Shoot Edin’s secret spot for sunset

Payment schedule:

There are only 6 spots and we will sell out. Please scroll down to sign up.

The fee for the workshop is $325 Per person.

The tuition is due up front and there are no refunds.



What is NOT included:

Entry to the park ($20.00 per vehicle), meals, travel and local 
transportation to shooting locations are not included. Please bring your
 own lunch and plenty of water. Space is limited.

A follow-up email with schedule details, recommended gear and a liability release will be sent to registered photographers.

What IS included:
	An incredible, unforgettable experience, full of adventure with amazing people and loads of great photos!!!

What you need to bring:
	A camera, a tripod, a wide angle lens (preferably) its ok if you do not 
have one. A zoom lens (kit lenses are ok). Most importantly a great 
attitude.

title: Botanical Perfume 101: The power of scents on our mindsets
description:
Smell good, Smell well! Let us take you to a journey to the amazing and complex world of aromatherapeutic perfume-designing. 

ABA LOVE APOTHECARY invites you to create a pure botanical perfume oil blend to tune into your truest self.

In this class you will: • Explore a variety of treasured oils and fundamental ingredients  • Cover top, heart and base notes and how they relate to each other  • Discuss the unique energy of each essential oil & the personal connection to oils  • Discuss aromatic character & scent profiles.

By the end of class, students will have created a 10ml botanical blend with their newfound olfactory finesse!

Start off with a spa-like foot soak…to experience before you create!  2. Learn about a variety of salts, seaweeds used in bathing rituals and their benefits  3. Discover benefits of different essential oils and carrier oils and how to blend them  4. Create a customized blend of essential oils to embrace the Winter season – think woodsy and fresh

All material provided (packaging and ingredients)  Light snacks, tea and refreshing white wine sangria will be served!

title: Jewelry Making: Rose Quartz Bracelet
description:
Kick back, relax, and have a blast making gemstone bracelets that give back in a beautiful way!

50% of the proceeds collected through this class will be donated to the children Ubuntuu sponsors at the orphanage.

In this class you will:

1. Learn how to make a natural Rose Quartz bracelet with gold charm (charms will vary as there will be several options for you to choose)

2. Be provided with all tools and materials to create your very own bracelet

3. Receive one-one-one instructions from Joslyn

4. Listen to some good tunes

5. Learn briefly about the children of Ubuntuu sponsors and where your class contribution is going

By the end of the class, you will go home with your very own gemstone bracelet that you can wear yourself and brag to everyone about how you made it, or give it as a gift!!

Joslyn Fecik is the founder of Ubuntuu, an ethical jewelry line that sponsors several children at an orphanage in Haiti and provides back to school shoclarships for middle schoolers in NYC. The Ubuntuu belief is that if you give love, you can change the world. Come join our little love community and help us make a difference in a precious child’s life! <3

title: Valentine's Day with a Romantic Dinner & Cruise!
description:
Celebrate Valentine's Day with a romantic Dinner & Cruise!Make a romantic memory of the vibrant Budapest and bring the one you love to our Romantic ship cruise!Our special Valentines Day Cruise will feature a welcome champagne, delicious warm buffet dinner, another drink, live gipsy and Hungarian music, a romantic atmosphere and a small present for you and your beloved Partner at the end of the cruise!Budapest has many faces. This vibrant city calms down a little bit at nights, lights are lit up, and a new city comes out from the twilight. We created this program for those who would like to enjoy the wonderful view of the city swimming in lights in a romantic candlelight atmosphere, and have a romantic dinner on a boat with live music. The meals are prepared by European, and world champion food sculptor, Molnárka Péter, who is a true artist. He adds a creative touch to the already outstanding Hungarian and international cuisine served on our ships, placing emphasis on the harmony of color and form.The salon music is performed by 3 members of the Zoltán Kodály Awarded Hungária Folk Orchestra, including the world-famous violinist Zsigmond Vidak who is the owner of the Bronze Merit Cross of the Hungarian Republic.We will take you on a 2-hour long cruise on one of our air-conditioned ships. After dinner you can also admire the panorama from the open upper deck of the ship.Menu Cold entriesSpiced cottage cheese cream and
traditional greaves cream SoupsAlföld style goulash with small

title: Midnight in Paris Winter Ball
description:
A FRENCH 1920's BALL HOSTED BY BELLMONTE LIFE.

Step on to the streets of Paris, go back in time and channel your inner Ernest Hemingway or Zelda Fitzgerald for our Midnight in Paris Winter Ball.

1920'S Paris will be brought to life as you walk into the venue. Get your tails and flapper dresses ready for a spectacular evening. Inspired by Woody Allen's Oscar-nominated film, Midnight in Paris. Plan on being transporting back to 1920 Paris right when you walk into the majestic Capitale. Bringing back the glory days of Cole Porter, Josephine Baker, Zelda and F. Scott Fitzgerald, Ernest Hemingway, Picasso and Dali's 1920's Paris.

Midnight in Paris will offer guests complimentary Parisian canapes, with all the live attractions of the real 1920s in decadent era of Joie De Vivre. 

The Ball will take place at the historic Porchester Hall, a 1920 grade II listed art deco building where the venue will be transformed into an A-List haven.

Enjoy a sumptuous evening of cocktails and dancing at what is sure to be the event of 2017.

Looking forward to a brilliant night.

Bellmonte Life.

description:

Tickets: $12, available online starting Feb 3 & at the door, includes access to ROM exhibits. Open to the public, all ages welcome!

About Wednesday Management:
Wednesday is an artist management company based in Toronto representing Ralph, Saya, & Charlotte Cardin.
Wednesdaymgmt.com

About RALPH
Blending disco, pop, synth, and soul, RALPH (aka Raffa Weyman) is a fusion of 1970’s bass,1980’s style pop keys, contemporary vocal melodies and fresh synth sounds. Think Sade meets Donna Summer meets Stevie Nicks. Having performed at the Danforth Music Hall and the AGO Massive Party, with over 3 million plays on Spotify and featured as one of Spotify's "Top 17 Artists to Watch in 2017", Ralph continues to create buzz within the Toronto music scene. 

twitter.com/songsbyralph
instagram.com/songsbyralph
https://soundcloud.com/songsbyralph

About Babygirl
Babygirl is Kirsten Clark and Cameron Breithaupt, a pop songwriting duo based out of Toronto. Exclaim! Premiered their debut EP “As You Wish” in 2016, writing “[As You Wish]... channels melancholy into melodic dream pop gems.” CBC also gave the EP acclaim, calling the opening track “It’s Getting Late” an Earworm that just will not go away.” Babygirl will be performing at CMW 2017 and are currently writing and recording new music. 

https://soundcloud.com/babygirlband/sets/as-you-wish-ep

About Hoodlem
Hoodlem, widely known as Australia's front runner of experimental soul and alternative R&B has recently re-located to Toronto, Canada.  In 2016, coverage across popular music media outlets like FADER, NYLON and Pigeons & Planes praising her captivating production and stingingly catchy vocals lead to various festival appearances and a European Co-Headline tour. Hoodlem's quiet yet urgent momentum increases as she gears up for the release of her second EP in 2017.

https://twitter.com/hoodlemmusic
https://soundcloud.com/hoodlemmusic

title: A Night With Pleasence: Alexander Moskos, ZONES, Doom Tickler
description:
The Music Gallery and Pleasence Records present
A Night With Pleasence feat. Alex Moskos + ZONES + Doom Tickler

Saturday, February 11, 2017
Doors: 7pm | Concert: 8pm
The Music Gallery, 197 John St.
Tickets: $15 Regular | $10 Members/Students |$13 Advance at musicgallery.org

Pleasence Records, co-founded by James Lindsay and Deirdre O’Sullivan, is a label dedicated to underground experimentation based in Toronto. The music walks a fine line between pop and experimental, respecting the past while looking forward to (im)possible futures. This showcase also promises immersive visuals from multidisciplinary artist Vanessa Rieger (co-founder of The White House Project and the safe space project Nightlifeguard) and Randy Gagne aka Man Made Hill, last seen here as Randy the Tongue in performance art ensemble Stillboys.

Alexander Moskos is a long-standing participant in Montreal’s experimental music community. He has performed and recorded his own songs under the name Drainolith, with the noise rock band AIDS Wolf. Moskos has toured constantly over the past few years and released recordings on labels like NNA, American Tapes, and Drag City. This show is a rare solo piano outing, drawing from his first album of solo piano compositions, Military Terms, released on Pleasence Records in 2015. 

ZONES began as a sphere of sonic exploration established in the summer of 2012 by Toronto-based multi-media artist Derek McKeon. Working as ZONES, McKeon weaves hypnotic loops and psychedelic textures together to create a marbling of pop hooks in a kaleidoscopic haze. ZONES’ latest album, After Image, was released on Pleasence Records in 2016. 

Doom Tickler, Leslie Predy, is a Toronto-based artist who strives to create a primal musical experience that pushes the limits of sounds a human body can create. She utters twisted vocals from another planet, like all the cats on the internet blended into a digital grinder. These are the sounds of your stomach turning, bubbling like a soup & eating itself. This is dark, foreboding music.

Visuals sponsored by MOOG audio

title: Valentine's Day Date Night with Tablespoon Cooking Co.
description:
Looking for a different way to spend Valentine’s Day? Come join us for our Valentine’s Day Date Night cooking class. Don’t worry, it won’t be cheesy! 

In this class, you’ll work with your Valentine to make a fun and romantic dinner. At the end, we will all sit down and eat together. 

The atmosphere will be fun and convivial and we’ll have beer and wine. There will be snacks as you arrive and we’ll eat and drink throughout class.

We are selling this class by couple because we will work in pairs to cook the meal. However, feel free to come with a friend, parent, or whomever you would like to spend Valentine’s Day with… all are welcome! 




Important Event Details

CLASS FORMAT: This is a semi hands-on class. We will all work together to cook the recipes. Everyone will get their hands dirty and be involved in each recipe. This class is limited to 16 students.

SKILL LEVEL: All skill levels are welcome! From beginners to expert chefs, this class is for everyone.

FOOD: There will be a welcome snack for when you arrive and then we will eat throughout class. You’ll get to taste everything we are preparing.

ALLERGIES AND DIETARY RESTRICTIONS: Please let me know of any allergies or dietary restrictions IN ADVANCE and we can talk about accommodations.

DRINKS: I will provide local craft beer, wine, and bottled water. You’ll also get to taste the cocktails we make in class. You’re welcome to bring non-alcoholic beverages to class with you.

ADDRESS: Findlay Kitchen is located at 1719 Elm St. Cincinnati, OH 45202

PARKING: There is often street parking available or you can park in one of the Findlay Market lots. Parking info can be found on the Findlay Market website.

ARRIVAL: The classroom kitchen is all windows and located directly inside the main Findlay Kitchen entrance. You’ll see us when you walk up. The doors will be locked so just knock/buzz and we’ll let you in. We will be watching for arrivals so it shouldn’t be an issue. Please try to arrive around 5:30 - 5:45 pm so we can get started on time.

ATTIRE: Please wear closed toed, non-slip shoes. Please keep your hair pulled back or wear a hat. Otherwise, wear comfortable clothes that could potentially get a little dirty. I will provide aprons. Also, feel free to bring clothes if you need to change after work. There is a nice, clean bathroom where you can change.

WHAT TO BRING: Nothing!

Questions? Email jordan@jordanhamons.com

title: Mukti Freedom Gala 2017
description:
(((WE ARE SOLD OUT! If you're still interested, please email jennifer@rethreaded.com and you will be added to the waiting list. Last year we were able to accommodate many people on the waiting list with some creativity. You'll get first right of refusal if anything comes up.)))
	

Did you know...


	Human Trafficking is a $32 billion a year industry and a form of modern-day slavery that subjects women, children and men to force, fraud or coercion for the purpose of commercial sexual exploitation or forced labor. 
	More than 75% of women in the sex trade were sexually abused as children. 
	90% of women want to leave the sex trade but don’t have access to job training, counseling or treatment.

Rethreaded's mission is to unravel the effects of the sex trade by fighting business with business on a global and local level. We provide safe, viable and dignity-giving work to survivors of the sex trade allowing them to be who they were created to be.

We invite you to join us in the fight for freedom by helping break the cycle of the sex trade.

Mukti, which means freedom in Bengali, is our primary fundraising event of the year. 400 leaders from the Jacksonville community come to enjoy an evening of shopping (Rethreaded’s Pop-up Store + Silent Auction), dining and dancing while raising money to support our Survivor Advocate Program, providing survivors with case management, mental health counseling, crisis counseling and weekly classes.

This year, the event will be hosted at the beautiful and newly renovated space, The Glass Factory, which was built in 1936 by Henry Klutho in downtown Jacksonville.

Event is 21+

Interested in sponsoring the event or want to find out about volunteer opportunities?

Contact us at mukit@rethreaded.com,

title: Email Marketing Day - London 2017
description:
Expand your email marketing knowledge and learn from some of the best in the industry...





Email Marketing Day 2017 from FreshMail on Vimeo.

You will start the day with FreshMail’s experts in the field of email marketing in a relaxed atmosphere. The aim is to teach and inspire marketers to create effective campaigns and to learn and understand the good practices required to achieve success. We’ll cover a variety of topics and at the end of the day you will have the knowledge you need to continue growing from strength to strength.- Vital elements of robust email strategy.- Email design that drives conversion- The importance of content marketing in lead generation- Behavioural analysis in email marketing to increase ROI




The Programme
09.15 - Registration open09.45 - 10.05 - New Trends in Email Marketing 2017 - Kay Lancucki, FreshMail10.05 - 10.15 - Q&A10.15 - 10.35 - Content Marketing in eCommerce - Tony Messer, Pickaweb10.35 - 11.00 - Panel and Q&A with Tony Messer and Bloggers11.00 - 11.30 - Coffee break / Networking11.30 - 11.50 - Progressive Enhancements for Email - Kristian Robinson, TWO Digital11.50 - 12.00 - Q&A12.00 - 12.20 - The Importance of eCRM in a B2B Environment - Phil Ireland, Watt Utilities12.20 - 12.30 - Q&A12.30 - 13.30 - Lunch13.30 - 13.50 - Time, Audience and Needs - Be on Spot with Email Marketing - Guy Hanson, Return Path13.50 - 14.10 - The Importance of Strategy in Email Marketing - Jenna Tiffany, Digital Marketing Association14.10 - 14.30 - Growth Hacking Tactics for Email Strategy Success - Kelly Bolton, Entrepreneur.com14.30 - 15.00 - Panel and Q&A with Guy Hanson, Jenna Tiffany & Kelly Bolton15.00 - 15.30 - Coffee break / Networking15.30 - 15.50 - Seamless Consumer Communications and Experiences - Deborah Womack, Principle Consultant15.50 - 16.00 - Q&A16.00 - 16.20 - Intelligent Personalisation - Jack Taylor, Smarkets16.20 - 16.30 - Q&A16.30 - Onwards - Drinks and Networking





 The Speakers

Kay LancuckiFreshMail

Kay Lancucki has several years of experience in Marketing. He often helps SME’s to implement proven email and digital marketing strategies that drive ROI. Kay also consults with larger companies on email marketing automation to reduce costs and improve personalisation. As well as helping companies to optimise their email marketing results, he organises email marketing workshops and is a speaker in the field of online marketing.





Guy HansonReturn Path

Guy is a passionate advocate for intelligent use of customer data to drive responsive email programs. With a knowledge base that now spans nearly 15 years, he is a global e-mail expert and thought leader. Leading Return Path’s International Professional Services consulting team, Guy has worked with a broad range of clients across 5 continents to improve their email delivery, subscriber engagement and revenue generated. Outside of work, Guy is the Chairman of the DMA Email Council. In this role, he works with industry peers including brands, agencies, and service providers to promote the best interests of the email industry to a broader audience. He is also a regular contributor to the industry press.



Jenna TiffanyThe Digital Marketing Association

Jenna Tiffany has over eight years’ marketing experience within B2B and B2C sectors across a number of industries. She is an advisory board member of the DMA North Council, a member of the The Chartered Institute of Marketing (CIM) North East Board and a contributing hub member to the DMA’s Email Marketing Council. Jenna feels strong about developing and implementing digital strategies across all digital marketing channels including email, ecommerce, website development, social media, search, PPC and SEO. As an industry though-leader, she is often asked to comment on the latest trends and key industry topics for Smart Insights, PerformanceIn and Mediapost.



Jack TaylorSmarkets

Jack Taylor has worked for L'Oreal, Paul Smith, Universal Music and most recently a start-up betting exchange called Smarkets. From an email marketing perspective he has experience working towards a number of different objectives. At L'Oreal it was about loyalty and retention, at Paul Smith it was e-commerce and revenue, at Universal Music it was about high volume, high impact 'product' releases and at Smarkets the focus has very much been about customer journey flow.





Tony MesserPickaweb

Tony Messer is a the Co-founder and CEO of UK web hosting company Pickaweb. He specializes in helping small businesses, web designers, developers and agencies. He is a contributor to Entrepreneur, Business and Search Engine Journal, and the author of the Amazon best selling book "The Lazy Website Syndrome" which provides business owners with a clear, step by step approach for growing their online operations. Tony is passionate about developing a powerful, long term and sustainable content strategy that supports business objectives.





Kelly BoltonEntrepreneur Magazine

Kelly Bolton is the founder and director of Aggressive Growth Marketing. Known for unprecedented levels of ambition, drive and client service, Kelly has fuelled AGM and has taken it from a part-time start-up to one of the fastest rising stars among digital marketing firms in the UK. She loves nothing more than sharing her expertise in helping companies maintain a competitive edge in the rapidly-evolving information age.





Kristian RobinsonTwo - Digital Marketing Agency

Kristian is passionate about all things email, and is the Lead Email Developer at TWO Digital, a London based digital marketing agency specialising in B2B digital delivery. In 2015 he was listed in an article called '15 email designers to look out for', and was in Litmus’s ‘Top Email Design Thought Leaders on Twitter’. The 2016 has seen him appear as a guest speaker at Litmus TEDC, Email on Acid and Taxi for Email. This time his attention will turn to using progressive enhancements with CSS, considerations for creating a more user friendly experience in your email design, and how we can adapt user experience based on audience type and why it’s important.





Deborah WomackPrinciple Consultant

Digital and CRM Principle Consultant. For more than 20 years Deborah has been leading the transformation of global businesses into customer-focused enterprises by instituting CRM Strategies, Tools, and Techniques across Digital, Mobile and Social. Having worked with some of the world’s leading companies and brands such as SABMiller, Nokia, Sony, Marks and Spencer and Kimberly-Clark, Deborah applies a unique perspective to CRM solution design by focusing on understanding and solving the core business challenge faced by organizations today: delivering great experiences by building successful customer relationships in ever-changing, challenging landscapes.





Phil IrelandWatt Utilities

Phil Ireland, currently Head of CRM & Marketing Operations at WATT UTILITIES LTD. Phil has worked in various industries such as Retail, Trade, Energy, Charity and Education over the past 10 years, implementing eCRM strategies for SME and large enterprises. Passionate and very much in love with all things email, he has overseen companies generate millions in revenue for eCRM campaigns.

title: Conférence par Annie Marquier - le yoga de l'ame
description:
Expo Yoga vous propose de vivre une expérience unique : soyez connecté, nourri et inspiré !

Bien plus qu’un simple salon, Expo Yoga vous offre l’occasion de découvrir et d’approfondir différentes approches du yoga avec plus de 50 classes, ateliers et conférences s’adressant à tous les niveaux de pratique, que vous soyez débutant, intermédiaire ou expert en yoga.

Faites la connaissance de professeurs de yoga de renom (d’ici et de l’international), d’exposants inspirants et de produits adaptés à votre mode de vie.

Parcourez la salle d’exposition et rencontrez plus de 150 exposants issus du yoga, de l’alimentation, de la santé et des soins ainsi que de la mode et de la beauté.

title: Fox Mowing & Gardening
description:
Philip purchased a Jim’s Mowing franchise in Melbourne in 1989, before purchasing the Regional Franchise for South Australia in 1990, becoming the first ever Regional Franchisor in the Jim’s Group. He subsequently sold over 500 franchises over the next 15 years, before selling the Jim’s Mowing South Australian Regional Franchise in 2005. Philip also developed the second largest Jim’s Customer Contact Centre in Adelaide servicing five States and Territories and over 600 franchisees before selling this in early 2007. From May 2007 thru to October 2009, Philip worked for Jim's Group as the Divisional Manager for Jim's Mowing. Philip also consulted to the Jim’s Group National Office from September 2011 thru to February 2012.

Fox mowing is made up of passionate lawn and garden maintenance professionals with decades of experience under their belts. When you engage our services you know that you’re dealing with local operators. All our people live in the areas they serve, so they are locals serving locals. They know the lay of the land and what people living in their area actually like and want. When you get Fox to do the job, you know you’re supporting your local economy too, so whilst we are a growing company, you really are supporting a local business, just like any other city or country-based business. All our people go through thorough police checks and we are fully and comprehensively insured for the services they perform, so you never need to worry if they break something or hurt themselves that you might find yourself in a bad situation. We’re covered and you’re covered.

title: Gruppo Mundo
description:
Gruppo Mondo featuring Peter Primamore, Jerry Marotta and Fran Tokarz is a powerhouse Jazz & Rock band with a unique take on a wide variety of music. From straight ahead Swing and Latin Music to one of a kind re-imaginings of classic rock and unique originals, Gruppo Mondo delivers intense performances with unpredictable improvisations. Often augmented by spectacular guest artists,  Peter, Jerry & Fran combine their decades of deep musical experience into an extraordinary evening of music and entertainment.

Peter Primamore: Piano & Keyboards.  Peter is a multi-award winning, critically acclaimed artist & composer with an endless list of media credits to his name. His keyboard work ranges from Fiery and Ferocious to Quiet & Ethereal. He also likes to sort of sing on occasion. More on Peter: www.peterprimamore.com

Jerry Marotta: Drums & Percussion. Considered one of the world’s premier drummers, Jerry Marotta has recorded and toured with Peter Gabriel, The Indigo Girls, Hall and Oates, Tears For Fears, Elvis Costello, Paul McCartney, 10,000 Maniacs, Suzanne Vega and Joan Armatrading to name only a few. Through his extensive touring experience and performances on hundreds of albums Jerry has worked with many of the greatest producers in the world. More on Jerry www.jerrymarotta.com

Fran Tokarz: Rock Solid Bassist, Bandleader and New England Stalwart, Fran is the anchor holding down the groove. With Decades of live performances Internationally with innumerable groups & artists, Fran’s energy and personality light up the stage.

title: Chris Rock: Total Blackout Tour 2017
description:
Grammy and Emmy Award winning comedian, actor, director, writer and producer, Chris Rock, announced Tuesday a highly anticipated return to live comedy with an all-new tour. The TOTAL BLACKOUT TOUR 2017 kicks off on February 13, 2017 in Durham, NC at DPAC. By popular demand, third show added February 13, 2017. The first leg of the TOTAL BLACKOUT TOUR 2017 will be the acclaimed comedian’s first tour in over 9 years and will visit cities throughout the U.S. including Atlanta, Minneapolis, Denver, Houston, Detroit and more. More dates will be announced soon.  A full list of tour dates is below. Tickets go on sale now at www.livenation.com and other outlets.

Lauded by peers and critics alike, Chris Rock is one of our generation’s strongest comedic voices. As an actor, director, producer and writer he has created many memorable moments.

Rock returned in 2016 to host the 88th Annual Academy Awards. In the past year, he has directed HBO’s comedy special “Amy Schumer: Live at the Apollo.”

With a career spanning more than three decades, Rock has enjoyed ongoing success in both film and television as a comedian, actor, writer, producer and director.  In 2014 he led the ensemble cast of “Top Five,” a critically acclaimed comedy feature that he also wrote and directed.  In 2009 Rock ventured into the documentary world as a writer and producer of “Good Hair,” and in 2014 he executive produced “Eat Drink Laugh: The Story of the Comic Strip,” a documentary recounting the history of one of New York’s most famous comedy venues.  His feature acting credits include the “Grown Ups” and “Madagascar” franchises, “Head of State,” “Nurse Betty,” “CB4”, “Death at a Funeral,” “I Think I Love My Wife,” “2 Days in New York,” “Dogma” and “New Jack City.”

His television work includes serving as executive producer, writer and narrator for the series “Everybody Hates Chris,” which ran from 2005 to 2009, and as a cast member on “Saturday Night Live” from 1989-1993.

Rock has won four Emmy Awards, three Grammy Awards and is a New York Times Best-Selling Author. In addition, he received two nominations for the 2016 Emmy Awards, for Outstanding Director for a Variety Special for “Amy Schumer: Live at the Apollo,” and Outstanding Special Class Program for the 88th Annual Academy Awards.

For Mature audiences.

Contains strong language and adult themes. Not recommended for children or preteens. Parental discretion advised.

title: Young The Giant w/ Lewis Del Mar at The Bourbon
description:
w/ Lewis Del Mar
Doors: 7 p.m. || Show: 8 p.m.
All Ages || $27.50: Advance || $32: Day of Show
$2 Minor Fee at the door
Tickets On-Sale Friday, November 18th @ 10 a.m.

The Bourbon Theatre presents...

::: Young the Giant :::

There comes a time in a young band's life when they hit that sweet spot where their voice, their sound, and their unity as a band gel perfectly. For Los Angeles-based indie rockers Young the Giant, that time is now. This trifecta of musical magic manifests itself on the band's third album, Home of the Strange, on Fueled by Ramen. 

"With these new songs, we've fully embraced what it is to be lyricists. We're not trying to combine fiction writing and lyricism anymore," explains singer Sameer Gadhia, who minored in fiction writing at Stanford University where he studied human biology before dropping out to pursue music. “We’ve also taken a collective approach to the thematic and lyrical development of each song on this album. Most of these songs came together during the demo process at either Seahorse Studios in downtown Los Angeles where Francois, Eric and I would spend hours collaborating over coffee on the rooftop, or at our producer’s home studio in West Los Angeles where we would do the same on his back patio. We used to view songwriting more like being a fly on the wall and not being in the story. But, on this record, we're in the story more than ever. It's personal, but universal at the same time."

The new record not only displays the group's new heights as lyricists and communicators, but it shows a rich, musical growth for the band as well. "We've always struggled to really capture what we do live on record. We accomplish that on this release. Now that we're on our third album we finally figured out how we need to work together. It helped that we had a theme and we all kept on that path in one solid mindset throughout the process." 

The theme of Home of the Strange is of the modern American immigrant story. It's especially relevant to the quintet as they're from different ethnic backgrounds and most are immigrants or first-generation Americans. Gadhia is Indian-American, Jacob Tilley (guitar) is British, Eric Cannata (guitar/vocals) is a New Jersey-born Italian-Jewish, Payam Doostzadeh (bass) is Persian-American, and Francois Comtois (drums/vocals) is French-Canadian. But, it also speaks to anyone who feels like they don't belong, or feels marginalized, angry about the state of affairs of our nation (especially in this polarizing election year), or hopeless about a better future. 

On "Amerika," for instance, the band explores the idea of the American dream and how to reconcile that with the various cultures they each grew up with. The song, which USA Today named one of the 10 Best Songs of the Week, was inspired by Franz Kafka's unfinished novel of the same name. It's the story of a 16-year-old boy named Karl who flees Germany under uncertain circumstances looking for a better life in New York and struggles to find a place to belong between the two cultures. 

"We find ourselves searching for our own ethics in between the often-contradictory beliefs of this polarized American Modern Age and those of the romanticized cultures of our forefathers," reveals Gadhia, whom The New York Times declared "one of the great contemporary rock voices." "Our perspective is irreversibly tinged with this rhetoric of the immigrant conscience and guilt. Searching for the 'American dream' is to lust for excess, power, and sex. We realize that when we achieve our goals, they often leave us more hollow than before."

"Home of the Strange," meanwhile, is a tongue-in-cheek play on the national anthem. "I've always had to reconcile the ideals of my Indian culture that my parents tried to instill in me with what it means to be American and figuring out what my American dream is. There was always a conflict of where it is that I exist. Am I American? Am I Indian? I always felt that I was somewhere in-between. I wanted to find a place to belong."

"Something to Believe In" was inspired by conversations with students they met at colleges in 2015 while performing on tour. It’s about being brave enough to forge your own path if the one we're raised to follow fails. "Everybody wants something to believe in," he says. "But what many of us are taught to believe in - go to school, get a job, have a family - doesn't always work. Kids are coming out of college with serious debt and jobs are scarce. They're realizing the dream is broken. It can be liberating and scary at the same time to carve your own path instead." 

The album's most hopeful song, "Repeat," is a call to action to not repeat history. "The only times people tend to make big changes is when they must - when they are faced with something greater than themselves. Things seem bad now with environmental issues, the economy, the job market, but sometimes the best changes come when we are at our lowest," says Gadhia.

Musically, the band came into the recording sessions with a specific sonic vision. "We wanted a full, live band sound, but at the same time really direct and up-front. It's the perfect combination of old school and new school. It's like a contemporary hi-fi record. We finally achieved that live sound we'd been touching upon on previous records, but it's full realized on this one," says Gadhia of the sessions with producer Alex Salibian (Elle King, Mikky Ekko) and executive producer Jeff Bhasker (Kanye West, Jay Z, fun.), who won the 2016 Grammy Award for Producer of the Year for his work with Mark Ronson and Nate Ruess, among others.

The band also finally figured out how to truly write together as a band. "Most bands don't actually write together," notes Gadhia. "It's a great concept, but it wasn't until this record that we actually fully achieved it. Our new producer Alex really helped us get there. We realized the genesis of a song or its end point can come from any member. And we all switched around, too. We played different instruments. I played a Hammond organ on 'Amerika,' and Jacob played vibraphone while Francois sang the verse. Overall, Fran and Eric sang and wrote more this time around. It's really our most collaborative effort." 
 
Since the band's 2010 inception, Young the Giant has made a name for itself in rock as the "thinking man's band," winning over fans, radio, and press with their incendiary live shows, strong musicianship, and poignant lyrics. The band's 2010 self-titled debut, which reached No. 6 on the Rock and Alternative album charts, featured the RIAA Gold-certified hits, "Cough Syrup" and "My Body," which peaked at No. 2 and No. 4, respectively on Alternative Radio. The band's sophomore release 2014's Mind Over Matter hit No. 7 on The Billboard 200 and spawned the hits, "It's About Time," which reached No. 2 on the Alternative Radio chart and the title track, which hit No. 15. 

Even with chart successes, critical praise (Rolling Stone, Billboard), coveted television appearances (The Late Show with David Letterman, MTV Video Music Awards), and high profile festivals (Lollapalooza, Bonnaroo), Young the Giant still feel like they have a lot more to do and, more important, a lot more to say as a band.

"We have a platform and we have our own beliefs, but at the same time, what's amazing about songwriting, music, or literature is that it brings people together and it shows people that everyone has the same problems and wants the same thing. This record is really a call to consciousness to really understand our predicament," adds Gadhia.

title: Pierogi-Making Class with Babushka Pierogie
description:
Grab your rolling pins! Sarah Dworak, of Babushka Pierogies, will share her Babushka's (grandmother's) pierogi recipe that has been handed down through the generations. This class will outline all steps of the pierogi-making process, from making filling, forming and rolling dough, pressing pierogies, and finally cooking and serving the pierogies.

Pierogi varieties include potato cheddar and sweet farmers' cheese, and Sarah will also teach the class the process of making farmer's cheese. You'll receive recipe cards for both pierogi varieties, and all of the leftover pierogies to share with family and friends.
We ask that you bring a rolling pin, but we will have several extras on-hand if you do not have one.

title: Amélie - Midnight Madness
description:
AMELIE screens Friday (2/10) and Saturday (2/11). Tickets are $7.

Synopsis: Amélie is a fanciful comedy from Jean-Pierre Jeunet, the acclaimed director of A Very Long Engagement and The City of Lost Children. He invokes his incomparable visionary style to capture the exquisite charm and mystery of modern-day Paris through the eyes of a beautiful ingenue (Audrey Tautou). Her life changes course when she discovers an old box of childhood treasures, anonymously returns it to its rightful owner, and watches from a distance as his life is transformed by the discovery. Thus begins her odyssey: a series of inventive plans to straighten out other people's lives—mostly for the better (if they've earned it) and occasionally for the worse (if they deserve it). But she always hides behind a veil of mystery and anonymity, which works well for her, until she meets an intriguing young man (Mathieu Kassovitz). Will she have the courage to do for herself what she has done for others? (Fully subtitled)

title: Wills and Trusts - Planning for the Future
description:
For families of a disabled or vulnerable people it’s important to consider how to provide for that person if you are no longer there to care for them.  Having an up to date Will in place goes some way to protect them, but it also has the potential to create further problems.  For example, leaving a lump sum to a disabled person may put them in a vulnerable position or could result in their means tested benefits being affected.  Philip Warford will explain how Wills and Trusts can be used to protect the vulnerable and ensure benefits are not lost.  Philip will discuss:



Why make a Will


	How you can protect a disabled person using Wills and Trusts
	The choice of Guardians for minor children
	The choice of Executors and Trustees
	The use of Letters of Wishes
	Making Gifts in a Will

Why use a Trust


	When should you set up a Trust
	How to protect means tested benefits
	The choices to protect a vulnerable person



Trusts explained


	Life interest Trusts
	Discretionary Trusts
	Disabled Person’s Trust

title: 7th IRCESM 2017
description:
Call for Papers

For

(IRCESM 2017)

Dubai, UAE 

12th & 13th April 2017

www.ircesm.com 

7th International Research Conference on Engineering, Science & Management 2017 (IRCESM’17) will be held in Hyatt Place Hotel, Al Rigga, Dubai, UAE during 12th & 13th April 2017.

All full paper submissions will be peer reviewed and evaluated based on originality, technical and/or research content/depth, correctness, relevance to conference, contributions, and readability. The full paper submissions will be chosen based on technical merit, interest, applicability, and how well they fit a coherent and balanced technical program.

Journal Publication:



IRCESM’17 coordinates with authors and Journals to ensure high quality research could achieve esteemed publication. According to this only selected invited extended version of best quality papers presented in IRCESM’17 will be recommended for publication consideration for Scopus and ISI Indexed Journals, according to the participating Journal publishing policies and requirements.

Please submit your papers via email to ircesm@gmail.com.



Topics:

The organizing committee of IRCESM 2017 invites research scholars, academicians, scientists and industrialists worldwide to submit original unpublished manuscripts that illustrate research results, projects, surveying works and industrial experiences that describe significant advances in the following topics of interest include, but are not limited to:

Civil Engineering

• Modern Trends in Civil Engineering • Building Energy Conservation and Green Architecture • Bridge and Tunnel Engineering • High-rise Structure and Large-span Structure • Municipal Engineering • Town Planning • Water Resource Engineering • Transportation Engineering • Geotechnical Engineering

Mechanical Engineering

• Design and Manufacturing Engineering • Materials Science and Engineering • Mechatronics and Automation • Industrial and Systems Engineering • Textile and Leather Technology • Automobile Engineering • Production Technology • Avionics

Basic Science

• Crystal Growth of Advanced Materials • Advanced Numerical Algorithms • Applications of Computation as a Scientific Paradigm • Advanced Chemistry • Mathematical Modelling • Computational Physics & Biology • Quantum computation • Cryptography

LifeScience Engineering

• Bio-medical engineering • Bio-Nanotechnology • Robotics and Rehabilitation • Medical Imaging • Advancements in Medical Technology • Bio-Engineering

Electrical Engineering

• Electric Drives and Control • Power Generation, Transmission and Distribution • Smart Grids Technologies & Applications • Renewable Power Generation and its Efficient Utilization • Electricity Market in Smart Grid • Power System Engineering & its applications • Electrical Machines • Instrumentation Engineering

ICT

• Communication Networks and Security • Software Engineering • Signal Processing • Network Management • Cloud Computing • Parallel and distributed computing • Information theory • Machine learning • Next Generation Networks

Management

• Financial Management • Marketing Management • HR Management • Retail Management • E-Commerce Technologies • Strategic Management • Financial and Management Accounting • Business Statistics • Business communication • Enterprise Resource Planning

Computer Science and Applications

• Software Engineering • Computer Applications • Computer Networks • Algorithms and data structures • Program semantics and verification • Natural Language Processing • Theoretical computer science and algebra • Computational complexity, economics, geometry • Artificial Intelligence

Oil, Gas, Energy & Mining Engineering

• Drilling and Completion Technology • Geoscience • Energy Demand and Supply • Energy Sector opportunities and Challenges • Environmental & Health Aspects • Alternative Energy • Resource Utilization Issues • Metal Mining

 For more information about IRCESM 2017, please visit, www.ircesm.com or you are welcome to contact the organizing committee directly via email to ircesm@gmail.com.

title: Awaiting Oblivion | Tim Smith-Stewart & Jeffrey Azevedo
description:
Awaiting Oblivion—Temporary Solutions for Surviving the Dystopian Future we Find Ourselves Within at Present

Blurring the lines between fiction and reality, Awaiting Oblivion...follows the story of AO, an anonymous street artist who has tasked Tim and Jeffrey with the creation of a performance as a way to share AO’s “temporary solutions” for existing within our collapsing empire. Inspired by creative processes developed by the '60’s Fluxus art movement, each “temporary solution” is a visual/textual poem contained in a Flux-kit (a cigar box collaged with stenciled imagery and typewritten letters). We follow Tim, Jeffrey, and AO in a flurry of street art, secret messages, and performance scores in a poetic, radical fight for survival.

title: IdentityNorth 2017 Partnerships
description:
Partnership Information Package

IdentityNorth 2017:

Now is the time for Canada to step up. We have all the ingredients and participants required to build a future that is the envy of the rest of the world. Strong digital identity technologies, processes and partnerships will be the foundation of a robust digital economy. We call upon all attendees of IdentityNorth 2017 to seize the opportunity that is before us: affirm Canada’s place leading the development and adoption of robust, scalable, privacy-enhancing digital identity ecosystems that serve the needs of all stakeholders, securing digital transactions.

The IdentityNorth 2017 Agenda is currently in development. Presenters are invited to submit proposals for this two-day forum. Day One will feature presentations by leading identity and digital economy experts from Canada and around the world. That evening we will host The Leaders Dinner and Awards, honouring the visionaries who have led and continue to shape the Canadian and global identity space. Day Two is an “unconference” in which attendees leverage the incredible expertise and talent at IdentityNorth to collaborate to identify and tackle the hottest topics and thorniest challenges in digital identity.

Why Become a Partner

IdentityNorth is Canada’s leading forum for individuals and organizations interested in digital identity and the digital economy. It is an important platform to share the ideas and knowledge that will drive Canada’s digital future. The forum delivers high value content through its subject matter experts, keynotes and an “unconference” day - a participant driven event where attendees build the agenda and lead inspiring and insightful sessions on contemporary identity topics. Sponsoring IdentityNorth is the best way to engage the digital identification community and raise the level of brand awareness of your company and its role building Canada’s digital economy.

We look forward to seeing you at IdentityNorth 2017!

Aran Hamilton

description:
Call for Papers


For

Dubai, UAE 

1st & 2nd May 2017

www.icmest.com

 

4th International Conference on Management, Engineering, Science & Technology 2017 (ICMEST 2017) is a prestigious event organized with a motivation to provide an excellent international platform for the academicians, researchers, engineers, industrial participants and budding students around the world to share their research findings with the global experts. ICMEST 2017 will be held in Hyatt Place Hotel, Al Rigga, Dubai, UAE during 1st & 2nd May 2017.

All full paper submissions will be peer reviewed and evaluated based on originality, technical and/or research content/depth, correctness, relevance to conference, contributions, and readability. The full paper submissions will be chosen based on technical merit, interest, applicability, and how well they fit a coherent and balanced technical program.

Journal Publication:

 

ICMEST 2017 coordinates with authors and Journals to ensure high quality research could achieve esteemed publication. According to this only selected invited extended version of best quality papers presented in ICMEST 2017 will be recommended for publication consideration for Indexed Journals, according to the participating Journal publishing policies and requirements.

title: Range Ready
description:
This course is designed for students who either own guns they don’t handle often or that would like to shoot but are intimidated with handling the gun without understanding it’s functionality.  Students will handle a variety of guns. Eye dominance testing and dry fire practice ensure that by the time you show up to the range you are comfortable, confident, safe, and knowledgeable.
Safety
Loading and unloading
Single action / double action and de-cocking clarified
Slide racking
Grip, stance, site picture, and trigger technique basics
Assessing the condition of a handgun
Clearing malfunctions
Creating a ready to fire condition
Range etiquette
This class is NOT designed to create accuracy in shooting performance. This is simply to familiarize the students with how the gun functions and teach basic safety. For technique development resulting in accuracy please attend a Technique Skill Development Lab, pistol craft, or private package session.

title: Muddy Muggle Twin Cities
description:
Introducing the world’s FIRST obstacle course race inspired by the world of Harry PotterTM !

Join all of your mud-covered muggle friends as they navigate their way over obstacles that only a witch or wizard worth their wand would know how to overcome…fire-burning cauldrons, walls that appear to be 9 ¾ feet tall, quidditch quaffles flying through the air…all while being chased by demented dementors!  The 5k (3.1 mile) course is comprised of 12 wizarding obstacles to defeat, some of which may require a helping wand from a fellow witch or wizard. This is it. THIS is what you’ve been waiting for. Register today to secure your spot in what we anticipate will be a sold-out event!

THIS IS AN IMMERSIVE EXPERIENCE.

The Muddy Muggle is SO much more than just a 5k obstacle course race. Our magical gates open on the afternoon of Friday, September 22, 2017 to kick off the weekend festivities with live entertainment by Wizard Wrock bands and exciting Wizard Games in the festival village. Saturday is a FULL day of enchanting experiences beginning with the Muddy Muggle obstacle course race inspired by the world of Harry Potter. Spectators/festival goers can cheer on their favorite muggle from the sideline or spend the day browsing the shops on Horizontal Alley, participating in the numerous events and activities in Hogsbreath Hollow’s village square, or watching their favorite teams compete on the quidditch green. The choice is yours. On Saturday evening, you’ll want to come dressed to impress in your wizard best and join us for our Wizard Wrockfest and enjoy a mug of butterbeer. For those of you holding the “Prefect Pass,” you’ll join us under a canopy of stars for the Fantastic Feast, a seat-limited “farm to fork” feast filled with fresh locally, sourced flavorful faire.

As if things couldn’t possibly get any better, all Muddy Muggle participants also receive an event t-shirt, a finisher’s medal, free festival entry, and a mug of butterbeer (21 and older)!

Not just another obstacle course race! The Muddy Muggle is an immersive experience that puts YOU right in the heart of the action in our very own Hogsbreath Hollow!! Held over the course of one magical weekend, our festival gates open on the afternoon of Friday, September 22, 2017 to kick off the weekend festivities with live entertainment by Wizard Wrock bands and exciting Wizard Games in the festival village along the streets of Horizontal Alley. Saturday, September 23, 2017 offers a FULL day of enchanting experiences beginning with the Muddy Muggle obstacle course race inspired by the world of Harry Potter. Spectators/festival goers can cheer on their favorite muggle from the sideline or spend the day browsing the shops (vendors) on Horizontal Alley, participating in the numerous events and activities in Hogsbreath Hollow’s village square, or watching their favorite teams compete on the quidditch green. The choice is yours. On Saturday evening, you’ll want to come dressed to impress in your wizard best and join us for our Wizard Wrockfest where you can enjoy a refreshing mug of butterbeer! For those of you holding a pass that includes the Fantastic Feast, you’ll join us under a canopy of stars a seat-limited “farm to fork” feast filled with fresh locally, sourced flavorful faire.

Horizontal Alley

Browse the “shops” along the bustling Horizontal Alley where you’ll find everything that a witch or wizard could ask for. Catch a live demonstration by one of our numerous master craftsmen/women including candle and soap making, glass blowing, blacksmithing, and wand making! In need of a new wand? Don’t forget to stop by our wand shop where the “wand chooses the wizard.” Need to hone a few of your magical skills? Participate in potions class, divination, dark arts defense, and wizard dueling!

Village Activities

Come join the fun and participate in all that our festival has to offer! Here’s a partial list of what you’ll find in our festival square!

Hay Maze
Pumpkin Chunkin Contest
Wizard Chess
House Cup Trivia Competition
Broom Races
“Whomping Willowbroom” Mechanical Broom Challenge
Costume Contest
Autumnal Soccer
Kids’ Inflatable Obstacle Course
Horcrux Hunt
Campfire Stories in Quidditch Pitch Campground
Trick-or-Treating for our young witches and wizards
Wide World of Quidditch

Calling all quidditch athletes and fans!! Join us in Quidditch Pitch Park for all things quidditch! Demonstrations, matches, and gear expo…we have it all!

From the 1970s thru the 80s, Discoteque nightlife was the place to be and be seen in the US and all around the world! Clubs in the NYC metro area were instrumental in the growth of disco music and urban nightclub culture.
	

Jams In The City Entertainment and the Funkytown Classic Disco & Freestyle Meetup kicks off the New Year its monthly Wednesday night residency at El Patron Restaurant and Bar in AC with the CAPRICORN BIRTHDAY BASH.

If you want to elevate your Super-Fly party experience and stand out from the crowd, then you should consider sponsoring a song at the upcoming Super-Fly Disco party. The party is only weeks away and we only have up to 10 songs that are available for sponsoring. title: Room Escape Amsterdam
description: Play live Room Escape in the original historic ammunition storage in Amsterdam West. Room Escape Amsterdam is one of the best trips for both individuals and businesses. The concept is very simple, you are together with your friends, colleagues or relatives imprisoned in one of our 4 Rooms. A Room Escape game lasts a maximum of 1 hour but the sport is, of course, to escape from the room as quickly as possible. You do this by solving puzzles, clues and good cooperation.Room Escape Amsterdam is powered byKunstgras Events and currently has 4 rooms in Amsterdam West. Each of the 4 rooms are in the same building, each room has its own theme. We are often asked which room is best? This is very dependent on your group. Read for yourself the description of the rooms, “The Armory“, ” The Vault “,”Quarantine “and” Into the Woods “. There you can see directly the availability and it is possibly to book a room.Room Escape Amsterdam is located in Amsterdam West, you can park for free. There is a direct bus from Amsterdam Central Station that takes about 30 minutes. You can park your car in the parking lot directly to the left when you arrive on our location, when it is full you can park on the street outside the premises. It is not allowed to park on the property.The site in 1800 Roeden is an area that is also used by many artists and craftsmen, they are very fond of their privacy, we kindly ask you to respect this if you are our guest.Room Escape Amsterdam Our location is suitable for both individuals and businesses accommodate from 2 to 100 people. You can combine your Room Escape adventure with a meeting, drinks, BBQ, workshops or other team building activities, Kunstgras Events likes making a custom quote for you that meets your needs.

description:
Call for Papers

(ICSTEM 2017)

http://www.icstem.com/ 

The 7th International Conference on Science, Technology, Engineering and Management 2017 (ICSTEM 2017), is a premier event that address the new advancements and challenges in the field of Science, Engineering and Technology. ICSTEM 2017 will be held in Hyatt Place Hotel, Al Rigga, Dubai, UAE during 2nd & 3rd April 2017.

It aims to bring together leading academicians, Scientists, Researchers, Scholars and Students to exchange and share their Knowledge, experiences and research results on the aspects of advancements in Sciences, Technological, Engineering and Management. This forum will provide opportunity to network and discuss the practical challenges encountered and the solutions adopted in their respective domains worldwide.



Journal Special Issues:

ICSTEM 2017 coordinates with authors and Journals to ensure high quality research work could achieve esteemed publication. According to this initiative all the registered papers in ICSTEM 2017 will be recommended for publication consideration with Indexed Journals according to the participating Journal publishing policies and requirements.

title: 5 Day 3D Printing & Additive Manufacturing Masterclass
description: The goal of this course is to present a comprehensive overview of AM, spanning from fundamentals to applications and technology trends, and with strong focus on high-performance materials. Participants will learn the fundamentals of AM of polymers, metals, composites, and biomaterials, and will realize how process capabilities (rate, cost, quality) are determined by the material characteristics, process parameters, and machine designs. Application areas including aerospace components, electronics, medical devices, and consumer products will be discussed via detailed examples and case studies. Particular emphasis will be placed on metal- and powder-based AM technologies, and related design principles and process standards to achieve high-performance materials and novel properties via AM. Lab sessions will provide hands-on experience with a variety of state-of-the-art AM equipment. Participants will design, fabricate, and measure test parts, and will perform experiments to explore process limits. The course will conclude with discussion of how AM will influence existing business models in design and manufacturing, will pose major opportunities and needs for advancement.

title: Avenged Sevenfold + Special Guests: Disturbed & Chevelle - Valby Hallen - Udsolgt venteliste
description:
AVENGED SEVENFOLD + SPECIAL GUESTS: DISTURBED & CHEVELLE
VALBY HALLEN
LØRDAG 4. MARTS 2017

I 2013/2014 cementerede Avenged Sevenfold deres status som et af verdens fremtrædende headline bands ved at spille udsolgte arenaer i Storbritanien og Europa, inklusiv Londons Wembley Arena, The Hartwall Arena i Helsinki og Forum i Milano. De optrådte også på Tysklands Rock Am Ring samt Rock Im Park, samt et ærefrygtindgydende headline slot på Download Festival 2014. Sidst bandet besøgte Danmark i 2013 spillede de en udsolgt koncert i Falconer Salen.

Nu annoncerer bandet yderligere datoer til deres massive Europatour der starter i Dublin den 6. januar 2017.                       
Bandet har Disturbed med som Special Guests på hele touren, med In Flames der åbner i UK, og Chevelle i resten af Europa.

AVENGED SEVENFOLD opnåede succes verden over med en række populære albums – inklusiv deres 2005 platinsælgende gennembrud ”City Of Evil”, 2007s ”Avenged Sevenfold” der toppede Billboard Alternative, Hard og Rock lister, og to på hinanden følgende nummer 1 på Billboards Top 200 Album chart. ”Nightmare” (2010) og deres seneste ”Hail To The King” – opnåede Diamant, Platin og Guld status for albumsalg i næsten et dusin lande. De har også haft en række top 10 singler af forskellige formater, inklusiv  “Bat Country,” “Almost Easy,” “Scream,” “Nightmare,” “Welcome To The Family,” “So Far Away,” og “Hail To The King,” og “Shepherd of Fire.” Bandet der udspringer fra Huntington Beach, Californien, er blevet kendt for deres spektakulære live shows, der ofte udsælger arenaer verden over og headliner nogle af de største og mest prestigefyldte festivaler. I november 2012 lavede de en hidtil uset appearance som karakterer i Call of Duty Black Ops 2 – det bedst sælgende videospil nogensinde, der indeholdt bandets optræden af ”Carry On”, som er skrevet specielt til spillet.

Avenged Sevenfold udgav selv action-eventyr mobil-video-spillet Hail To The King:Deathbat der fik fantastiske anmeldelser, med det musikalske koncept og spil skabt udelukkende af bandet selv. Avenged Sevenfold optrådte i butikker og hjem verden over som featured pre-launch artist i 2015s Guitar Hero: Live including an industry first playable live performance.

De Grammy-nominerede hard rock Titans, DISTURBED returnerer til rockscenen efter en 4 års pause, med det anmelderroste #1 album ”Immortalized”. Albummet er bandets femte på hinanden følgende US #1, og har allerede kastet tre store #1 hits af sig, “The Vengeful One” (videoen har pt over 22 millioner views), ) “The Light”, og den globale sensation, deres stærke version af Simon & Garfunkels klassiker “The Sound of Silence” (82 millioner views på YouTube), som også gik nummer 1 på både Rock og Mainstream US rock radio.
Bandet blev dannet i Chicago i 1996, og det multi-platin sælgende DISTURBED der består af David Draiman [vokal], Dan Donegan [guitar], Mike Wengren [trommer], og John Moyer [bas] – har scoret tretten nummer 1 singler på Active Rock Radio. Deres firdobbelte-platin sælgende debut (fra 2000) ”The Sickness” cementerede deres ankomst som forgangsmænd på hardrockscenen. Den status konsoliderede de efterfølgende med Grammy Award nominering samt guld-, platin- og dobbeltplatin certificerede albums. Se videoen til “The Sound of Silence” her: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u9Dg-g7t2l4

title: meilleurs Brouilleur gps de signal
description:
Ce produit est en stock maintenant, nous garantissons l'expédition dans les 24 heures et offrent une garantie d'un an pour tous nos produits. Apporté par le leader des dispositifs de sécurité et des meilleurs Brouilleur GSM de signal.Remarques importantes concernant la distance de brouillage: Les distances de brouillage mentionnées sur le site Web ne sont que pour la référence du client. La distance de brouillage réelle sera modifiée en fonction de la puissance du signal et de l'emplacement d'utilisation et si les charges sont complètes, etc.Remarques importantes pour les brouilleurs portables sans ventilateur de refroidissement: N'utilisez pas le brouilleur lorsqu'il est en charge, sinon il brûlera le brouilleur car il n'a pas de ventilateur intégré. Si en raison de ce facteur en raison de la rupture du brouilleur 4g , le client perdra l'autorité de répartition libre.Ce qui est important, c'est que ce brouilleur peut également être utilisé pour personnaliser les bandes de fréquences que vous souhaitez. Bienvenue à fournir des fréquences et nous allons personnaliser pour vous.



Un dispositif de brouillage GPS ou un brouilleur GPS est généralement un petit émetteur autonome qui génère un signal d'interférence de 1575,42 Mhz sur un rayon de 5 à 10 mètres.Habituellement, l'utilisateur branche le Brouilleur GPS dans un allume-cigare et place l'unité suffisamment près d'un dispositif de poursuite GPS pour perturber le signal satellite GPS. Une fois sous tension, ils deviennent entièrement opérationnels en moins de 20 secondes. La puissance relativement faible et le temps de démarrage rapide permettent d'utiliser les brouilleurs uniquement si nécessaire. Les criminels les désactiveront dès que possible pour éviter la détection. Ces brouilleurs peuvent être achetés à bon marché sur Internet pour moins de 100 $.Une détection plus immédiate des brouilleurs est également disponible. Le module GPS des unités Geotab GO6 et GO7 dispose d'une fonction de détection de brouillage qui va déclencher la signalisation d'un journal de débogage par notre appareil. Cela peut être trouvé dans les détails du journal de MyGeotab, apparaissant comme: GpsJammingDetected.

Pour une surveillance simplifiée du brouillage et d'autres problèmes GPS, une règle d'exception peut être créée dans MyGeotab. Cette règle génère un rapport d'exception et peut déclencher une alerte ou un courrier électronique pour l'événement.

Dans une tentative de bloquer son employeur de suivre son camion de travail, résident du New Jersey est une amende de 32 000 $ pour l'utilisation d'un brouilleur GPS illégale.Les brouilleurs GPS sont illégaux aux États-Unis en raison de leur capacité à bloquer les communications importantes. Et pour un homme du New Jersey, le coût était beaucoup plus élevé que prévu.Tout d'abord, le Brouilleur Signal a empêché son employeur de suivre son allégeance pendant son quart de travail. La société qu'il travaille pour les dispositifs de suivi GPS installés sur tous les camions de travail, y compris celui qu'il conduisait. Ils ont fait cela afin de surveiller l'emplacement des camions et d'autres données, et être sûr que le temps de l'entreprise a été utilisé avec sagesse.

title: Cheap Trick
description:
2016 Rock & Roll Hall of Fame inductee, Cheap Trick is part of the fiber of American music, inspiring and delighting generations with their unique union of massive melodies and razorblade riffs, their own special brand of mischievous wit and maximum rock ‘n’ roll. Their greatest hits include: 

•	“I Want You To Want Me”
•	“I’m Not Gonna Miss You” 
•	“Dream Police”
•	“Surrender”
•	“California Man”

Frontlined since 1974 by Robin Zander (vocals, rhythm guitar), Rick Nielsen (lead guitar), and Tom Petersson (bass guitar), the Rockford, IL- born band is set to impact still another era with the spectacular new BANG ZOOM CRAZY…HELLO, their 27th studio collection and first in more than five years. 
After more than half a decade away from the studio, Cheap Trick was fired up and ridiculously prolific, cranking out close to 30 new tunes over two pair of sessions in Los Angeles and Nashville. Tracks like “No Direction Home” hit hard as a teenage crush’s kiss, affirming the eternal strength of Cheap Trick’s smart, sly, sometimes sarcastic songcraft. Each member has skin in the songwriting game, contributing elements – a riff, a chorus, a hook that won’t stop – which are then jammed into three-and-a-half minute pop perfection by the entire unit, ensuring everybody’s respective two cents are represented in every finished tune.

title: City Game Amsterdam
description:
City Game Amsterdam
GPS City Game is powered by  Kunstgras Events and Organizes city games throughout Europe. During a GPS City Game you will be, divided into teams, and battle with your colleagues, family or friends. Each team utilizes our app, this can be on your phone or tablet and on a phone or tablet supplied by us. Each game has its own story line, think of a GPS pub crawl, City scavenger hunt or real life Snakes and ladder.

City GPS Game optionsThere are two different options for organizing your event1.) Fully catered including counseling, tablets and prize for the winning team by Kunstgras Events.2) "Do it yourself" in which you play a game on your phone or tablet without guidance from us.

City Gaming in Amsterdam with your groupCity Games in Amsterdam are for groups of 10 to 1,000 participants. You may combine your City Game adventure with other activities, workshop, meeting, lunch or dinner.

City Game asmterdam on the scooter, bicycle or rickshawYou can also play your City Game in Amsterdam on a scooter, bicycle or even a rickshaw. This gives an extra dimension to the game and you quickly from one to the next marker. We can arrange transport for you or you can use your own bicycle to come to the meeting point, please keep in mind that we need to know this in advance.

To give you an idea of the possibilities, you can see an example below of an event we did for 120 NIKE employees in Amsterdam.



You can combine your City Game in Amsterdam with a meeting, Drinks and BBQ, workshop, childrens party Amsterdam ofr one of our other teambuilding activities like Bubble Football Amsterdam, RoomEscape Amsterdam, Laser Tag Amsterdam, For outings in Haarlem you can visit Eventlabel.

title: Horizon Festival 2017
description:
Horizon Festival 2017
Arinsal, Andorra
Sun 26 March — Sun 02 April, 2017

120 DJs and Live acts / 30 Parties / 7 Nights / 2 Mountains / 1 Amazing Ski Party

Floating Points • Motor City Drum Ensemble • Ben UFO • Mala • ONEMAN • KiNK • Midland • AJ Tracey • The Craig Charles Funk & Soul Show • Romare • Riot Jazz • Yussef Kamaal • Om Unit • MUMDANCE • Icicle • Jasper James • Josey Rebelle • Dan Shake • Avalon Emerson • Hybrid Minds • Rockwell • Channel One Sound System • Jam Baxter • Technimatic • Courtesy • Cooly G • Eva Lazarus • Scott Garcia • Or:la • El-B • Moony • Jamie Rodigan • Wayward • Emerald • Bahia Haze • DJ Sammy B-Side • ETCH • Itoa • Bulu • FRNCH • DB • Visionobi • Joe Raygun Music • RØDRI PAN

http://horizonfestival.net/

Having outgrown its previous home in Bulgaria, Horizon Festival is set for an exciting new chapter with even more diverse and eclectic sounds, stunning views, incredible skiing and snowboarding terrain and unparalleled late-night parties at its new home in Andorra. Taking over the village of Arinsal, close to the borders of France and Spain, festival-goers can dive into the celebrated Horizon programme, with an eclectic musical selection of artists, DJs and live acts from across the musical spectrum.

At every corner, Horizon has become synonymous for its out-there and spectacular parties and 2017 will be no different. The Andorran mountains will play host to a stunning variety of experiences, from the whimsical escape of the Forest Parties, the second-annual Horizon Paintball Wars, the pinnacle highs of the mammoth Warehouse Parties and a mountain top avalanche arena with Champagne ice bar, snow yoga, acoustic sets and more.

Kicking off the festival will be a special Pre-Party in Barcelona, the main gateway to Andorra, on Saturday 25th March, providing festival goers with a stop-over club experience in one of Barcelona’s top party venues.

Horizon Festival is the definitive winter festival experience - with over 120 DJs, 30 Parties and 2 Mountains, Horizon has rapidly gained a reputation as Europe’s Greatest Ski Party.

For more info and tickets please visit —www.horizonfestival.net

description:
Dive headfirst into the legendary night life of Budapest with the very first Ruin Pub party card and save on your consumptions and entry!

Hungary’s trademark attractions, the ruin bars are waiting for you with open arms and dizzying eyes in various popular and underground locations around Budapest. www.icetms.net 

 

4th International Conference on Engineering, Technology, Management and Science 2017 (ICETMS 2017) is a prestigious event organized with a motivation to provide an excellent international platform for the academicians, researchers, engineers, industrial participants and budding students around the world to share their research findings with the global experts. ICETMS 2017 will be held in Hyatt Place Hotel, Al Rigga, Dubai, UAE during 12th & 13th April 2017.

All full paper submissions will be peer reviewed and evaluated based on originality, technical and/or research content/depth, correctness, relevance to conference, contributions, and readability. The full paper submissions will be chosen based on technical merit, interest, applicability, and how well they fit a coherent and balanced technical program.

Journal Publication:

 

ICETMS 2017 coordinates with authors and Journals to ensure high quality research could achieve esteemed publication. According to this only selected invited extended version of best quality papers presented in ICETMS 2017 will be recommended for publication consideration for Indexed Journals, according to the participating Journal publishing policies and requirements.

 

Please submit your papers via email to info.icetms@gmail.com.
